'''Max Emilian Verstappen''' ({{IPA-nl|ˈmɑks vɛrˈstɑ.pə(n)}}; born 30 September 1997) is a Belgian and Dutch<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.gptoday.net/nl/nieuws/f1/201020/jos-verstappen-over-de-nationaliteit-van-max |website=GP Today |title=Jos Verstappen over de nationaliteit van Max |trans-title=Jos Verstappen about the nationality of Max |access-date=9 October 2022 |language=nl |archive-date=9 October 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221009082210/https://www.gptoday.net/nl/nieuws/f1/201020/jos-verstappen-over-de-nationaliteit-van-max |url-status=live }}</ref> [[Auto racing|racing driver]] competing in [[Formula One]] and the [[2021 Formula One World Championship|2021]], [[2022 Formula One World Championship|2022]], and [[2023 Formula One World Championship|2023  World Champion]]. He [[Formula One drivers from the Netherlands|races under the Dutch flag]] in [[Formula One]] for [[Red Bull Racing]].

Verstappen is the son of former Formula One driver [[Jos Verstappen]], and former [[Karting|go-kart]] racer Sophie Kumpen. He had a successful run in [[karting]] and [[single-seater]] categories – including [[FIA Formula 3 European Championship|FIA European Formula 3]] – breaking several records.

At the [[2015 Australian Grand Prix]], when he was aged {{Age in years and days|1997|9|30|2015|3|15}}, he became the youngest driver to compete in Formula One. After spending the {{F1|2015}} season with [[Scuderia Toro Rosso]], Verstappen started his {{F1|2016}} campaign with the Italian team before being promoted to parent team Red Bull Racing after four races as a replacement for [[Daniil Kvyat]]. At the age of 18, he won the [[2016 Spanish Grand Prix]] on his debut for Red Bull Racing, becoming the youngest-ever driver and the first [[Formula One drivers from the Netherlands|Dutch driver]] to win a Formula One Grand Prix.<ref>{{Citation|title=Verstappen's Maiden Win {{!}} Spanish Grand Prix 2016|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hohuswdeznA|access-date=21 January 2022|archive-date=13 October 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221013203403/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hohuswdeznA|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/live/2016/may/15/f1-spanish-gp-live-lewis-hamilton-nico-rosberg|title=F1: Max Verstappen wins Spanish GP after Lewis Hamilton and Nico Rosberg crash – live!|last=Ostlere|first=Lawrence|date=15 May 2016|website=The Guardian|access-date=15 May 2016|archive-date=15 May 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160515143832/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/live/2016/may/15/f1-spanish-gp-live-lewis-hamilton-nico-rosberg|url-status=live}}</ref>

After winning the [[2021 Abu Dhabi Grand Prix]], Verstappen became [[List of Formula One World Drivers' Champions|Formula One World Drivers' Champion]] for the first time, being the first Dutch driver and the 34th driver to do so.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://racingnews365.com/how-verstappen-joined-f1s-list-of-world-champions|title=How Verstappen joined F1's list of World Champions|date=12 December 2021 |access-date=13 December 2021|archive-date=13 December 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211213045157/https://racingnews365.com/how-verstappen-joined-f1s-list-of-world-champions|url-status=live}}</ref> He won the next two consecutive Formula One championships in {{F1|2022}} and {{F1|2023}}. As of the {{Latest F1GP}}, Verstappen has had {{f1stat|VER|wins}} victories, {{f1stat|VER|poles}} pole positions and {{f1stat|VER|fastestlaps}} fastest laps. In addition to being the youngest Grand Prix winner, he holds several [[List of Formula One driver records|Formula One records]], including the [[List of Formula One driver records#Most wins in a season|most wins in a season]] and the [[List of Formula One driver records#Most consecutive wins|most consecutive wins]]. Verstappen is set to remain at Red Bull until at least the end of the 2028 season after signing a contract extension.<ref name=":3">{{Cite web |date=3 March 2022 |title=Max Verstappen signs bumper new deal with Red Bull until end of 2028 |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.breaking-verstappen-signs-bumper-new-deal-with-red-bull-until-end-of-2028.7Csixu7ehVLNr5mDgFQ1Q7.html |access-date=3 March 2022 |publisher=Formula One |archive-date=3 March 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220303100618/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.breaking-verstappen-signs-bumper-new-deal-with-red-bull-until-end-of-2028.7Csixu7ehVLNr5mDgFQ1Q7.html |url-status=live }}</ref>

==Personal life==
Max Emilian Verstappen was born on 30 September 1997 in [[Hasselt]], Belgium to [[Jos Verstappen]] and {{ill|Sophie Kumpen|nl}}.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://en.espnf1.com/f1/motorsport/driver/171391.html |title=Drivers / Max Verstappen |publisher=ESPN F1 |access-date=20 August 2014|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150321042436/http://en.espnf1.com/f1/motorsport/driver/171391.html|archive-date=21 March 2015}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Max Verstappen with his sister Victoria Jane Verstappen and his father Jos Verstappen|url=http://en.espnf1.com/f1/motorsport/image/217737.html|access-date=14 December 2020|publisher=ESPN UK|archive-date=13 October 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221013203349/https://www.espn.com/f1/|url-status=live}}</ref> Verstappen's parents separated when he was young, after which he lived with his father. His younger sister, Victoria, lived with their mother.<ref>{{Cite web|date=10 December 2021|title=How Max Verstappen's hard-nosed upbringing created a driver ready for war with Lewis Hamilton|url=https://inews.co.uk/sport/formula-one/max-verstappen-lewis-hamilton-dangerous-driving-1341419|access-date=21 December 2021|website=inews.co.uk|archive-date=21 December 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211221184551/https://inews.co.uk/sport/formula-one/max-verstappen-lewis-hamilton-dangerous-driving-1341419|url-status=live}}</ref> Verstappen has three younger half-siblings from his father; a sister, Blue Jaye, from Jos's second marriage and a brother and sister, Jason Jaxx and Mila Faye, from Jos's current marriage.<ref name=":2">{{Cite web|title=Jos Verstappen becomes a father for a fourth time|url=https://www.gptoday.net/en/news/f1/247258/jos-verstappen-becomes-a-father-for-a-fourth-time|access-date=21 December 2021|website=GPToday.net|date=2 May 2019 |archive-date=21 December 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211221184601/https://www.gptoday.net/en/news/f1/247258/jos-verstappen-becomes-a-father-for-a-fourth-time|url-status=live}}</ref> 

His family has a long association with motor sports: his father is a Dutch former Formula One driver, his Belgian mother competed in [[Kart racing|karting]],<ref name="racing family2">{{cite web|last1=Bonardel|first1=Cécile|date=18 August 2014|title=Verstappen's son in F1 in 2015|url=http://www.24h-lemans.com/en/news/24-hours-of-le-mans-previous-class-winner-jos-verstappen-s-son-in-f1-in-2015_2_2_1746_16741.html|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141129073628/http://www.24h-lemans.com/en/news/24-hours-of-le-mans-previous-class-winner-jos-verstappen-s-son-in-f1-in-2015_2_2_1746_16741.html|archive-date=29 November 2014|access-date=28 May 2019|website=24h-lemans.com}}</ref><ref name="nationality2">{{Cite news|last=Cornelissen|first=Marc|date=17 August 2014|title=Geen rijbewijs, wel in de F1|language=nl|trans-title=No driver's licence, yet in F1|work=Nieuwsblad.be|url=http://www.nieuwsblad.be/sportwereld/cnt/dmf20140816_01219423|access-date=12 December 2014|quote=Max heeft een Belgische moeder, is geboren in Hasselt, woont in Bree en reist met een Belgisch paspoort. Genetisch en cultureel is hij Belgischer dan de gemiddelde Rode Duivel. Maar racen doet hij met een Nederlandse licentie. 'Ik heb heel mijn leven in België gewoond, maar ik voel meer Nederlander. Door al dat karten trek ik meer met mijn vader op dan met mijn moeder. Ik zit gewoon altijd tussen de Nederlanders. [Max has a Belgian mother, was born in Hasselt, lives in Bree, and travels with a Belgian passport. From a genetic and cultural perspective, he's more Belgian than the average Red Devil. Yet he competes with a Dutch racing licence. 'I have lived in Belgium my entire life, but I consider myself more Dutch. As a result of my karting activities I spend more time with my father than with my mother. I'm always surrounded by Dutch people.']|archive-date=8 March 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150308132510/http://www.nieuwsblad.be/sportwereld/cnt/dmf20140816_01219423|url-status=live}}</ref> and his first cousin once removed, [[Anthony Kumpen]], competed in endurance racing and is a two-time [[NASCAR Whelen Euro Series]] champion currently serving as the team manager for [[PK Carsport]] in Euro Series.<ref name="racing family2" /> Although Verstappen has a Belgian mother, was born in Belgium and resided in [[Bree, Belgium]], he decided to compete with a Dutch racing licence. He stated he "feels more Dutch", having spent more time with his father than with his mother during his upbringing, and was always surrounded by Dutch people while growing up in [[Maaseik]], a Belgian town at the Dutch border.<ref name="nationality2" /> Verstappen said in 2015: "I actually only lived in Belgium to sleep, but during the day I went to the Netherlands and had my friends there too. I was raised as a Dutch person and that's how I feel."<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gpfans.com/nl/artikelen/41751/dit-is-waarom-max-verstappen-niet-onder-de-belgische-vlag-rijdt/|title=Dit is waarom Max Verstappen niet onder de Belgische vlag rijdt|website=GPfans|date=3 July 2019 |access-date=1 November 2020|archive-date=19 September 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200919153745/https://www.gpfans.com/nl/artikelen/41751/dit-is-waarom-max-verstappen-niet-onder-de-belgische-vlag-rijdt/|url-status=live}}</ref> In 2022, however, Verstappen stated that he appreciates both sides and is "half-half at the end of the day".<ref>{{cite web |last1=Khyati C |title="I'm half-half at the end of the day"- Max Verstappen opens up about relations with Belgium and Holland |date=3 September 2022 |url=https://www.sportskeeda.com/f1/news-max-verstappen-opens-belgian-dutch-roots |publisher=[[Sportskeeda]] |access-date=12 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230612223755/https://www.sportskeeda.com/f1/news-max-verstappen-opens-belgian-dutch-roots |archive-date=12 June 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref>

He competed in Formula One for more than a season before obtaining a road driving licence on his 18th birthday.<ref>{{cite web|title=Road legal at last! Verstappen passes driving test on 18th birthday|url=http://www.formula1.com/content/fom-website/en/latest/headlines/2015/9/verstappen-passes-driving-test-on-18th-birthday.html|publisher=Formula One|access-date=30 September 2015|date=30 September 2015|archive-date=31 July 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160731183946/http://www.formula1.com/content/fom-website/en/latest/headlines/2015/9/verstappen-passes-driving-test-on-18th-birthday.html|url-status=live}}</ref> Verstappen moved to [[Monaco]] the day after, in October 2015, and has lived there since and has said it was not for tax reasons.<ref name="GPNov15">{{cite news|url=http://www.grandprix.com/ns/ns32591.html|title=Verstappen moves out of home for Monaco|date=28 November 2015|work=GrandPrix.com|access-date=17 May 2016|archive-date=22 May 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160522214846/http://www.grandprix.com/ns/ns32591.html|url-status=live}}</ref> In November 2020, Verstappen bought a [[Dassault Falcon 900]]EX aircraft from [[Virgin Galactic]]. The aircraft is [[aircraft registration|registered]] PH-DTF and operated by Exxaero.<ref name=Falcon>{{cite web |url=https://www.aviation24.be/tour-operators/exxaero/formula-one-racing-driver-max-verstappen-acquires-former-virgin-galactic-private-jet/ |title=Formula One racing driver Max Verstappen acquires former Virgin Galactic private jet |first=Bart |last=Noeth |publisher=Aviation24 |date=20 November 2021 |access-date=26 January 2022 |archive-date=26 January 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220126173346/https://www.aviation24.be/tour-operators/exxaero/formula-one-racing-driver-max-verstappen-acquires-former-virgin-galactic-private-jet/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

In his free time, Verstappen enjoys [[sim racing]]. Having taken part in many sim racing competitions, Verstappen stated that it helps him with his real life racing keeping him "ready to go".<ref name="RacingNews365">{{cite web | title=How Verstappen uses sim racing to become a better driver | website=RacingNews365 | date=11 January 2022 | url=https://racingnews365.com/how-verstappen-uses-sim-racing-to-become-a-better-driver | access-date=16 January 2022 | archive-date=16 January 2022 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220116135001/https://racingnews365.com/how-verstappen-uses-sim-racing-to-become-a-better-driver | url-status=live }}</ref> Verstappen is a member of ''Team Redline''; a multinational sim racing team.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Team Redline › Max Verstappen|url=https://www.teamredline.com/work/max-verstappen/|access-date=22 January 2022|website=Team Redline|archive-date=22 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220122123254/https://www.teamredline.com/work/max-verstappen/|url-status=live}}</ref> Verstappen is a supporter of [[FC Barcelona]] and [[PSV Eindhoven]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Moerman |first=Christian |date=26 November 2021 |title=Verstappen over favoriete club FC Barcelona: 'Ik baalde van vertrek Koeman' |trans-title=Verstappen about favorite club FC Barcelona: "I was disappointed with the departure of Koeman" |url=https://www.f1maximaal.nl/max-verstappen/verstappen-over-favoriete-club-fc-barcelona-ik-baalde-van-vertrek-koeman |access-date=16 May 2022 |website=F1Maximaal.nl |language=nl |archive-date=31 May 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220531140907/https://www.f1maximaal.nl/max-verstappen/verstappen-over-favoriete-club-fc-barcelona-ik-baalde-van-vertrek-koeman |url-status=live }}</ref> Verstappen speaks three languages, Dutch, English and German, the latter of which he learned while karting with [[Michael Schumacher]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Ghorpade |first=Niharika |date=23 July 2022 |title=Max Verstappen reportedly learned karting with Michael Schumacher |url=https://www.sportskeeda.com/f1/news-max-verstappen-reportedly-learned-karting-michael-schumacher |access-date=23 July 2022 |website=sportskeeda.com |language=en |archive-date=13 October 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221013203400/https://www.sportskeeda.com/f1/news-max-verstappen-reportedly-learned-karting-michael-schumacher |url-status=live }}</ref> In September 2022, he was made an Officer of the [[Order of Orange-Nassau]] in recognition of his racing achievements.<ref name="auto">{{Cite web|url=https://nltimes.nl/2022/09/01/royal-honor-max-verstappen-appointed-officer-order-oranje-nassau|title=Royal honor for Max Verstappen: Appointed Officer in the Order of Oranje-Nassau|access-date=1 September 2022|date=1 September 2022|website=NL Times|archive-date=13 October 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221013203401/https://nltimes.nl/2022/09/01/royal-honor-max-verstappen-appointed-officer-order-oranje-nassau|url-status=live}}</ref> Verstappen has been dating [[Kelly Piquet]] publicly since January 2021.<ref>{{cite web |author1=Bethânia Nunes |author2=Marina Ferreira |title=Modelo Kelly Piquet assume romance com piloto da Fórmula 1 Max Verstappen |url=https://www.metropoles.com/colunas/claudia-meireles/modelo-kelly-piquet-assume-romance-com-piloto-da-formula-1-max-verstappen |website=Metrópoles |access-date=13 March 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210313152034/https://www.metropoles.com/colunas/claudia-meireles/modelo-kelly-piquet-assume-romance-com-piloto-da-formula-1-max-verstappen |archive-date=13 March 2021 |language=pt |date=1 January 2021 |url-status=live}}</ref>

==Junior career==

===Karting===
Verstappen started racing in karts at the age of four and competing in championships at the age of seven. In 2005 he competed in the Mini Junior championship of his home province of [[Limburg (Belgium)|Limburg]], Belgium<ref>{{cite web|title=Limburgs Kart Championship&nbsp;– Mini-Junior 2005|url=https://www.driverdb.com/championships/standings/limburgs-kart-championship---mini-junior/2005/|work=DriverDB.com|access-date=27 January 2014|archive-date=22 May 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210522154144/https://www.driverdb.com/championships/standings/limburgs-kart-championship---mini-junior/2005/|url-status=live}}</ref> and won the [[Flanders|VAS]] Championship in the same category. In 2006, he repeated his success. In 2007, Verstappen graduated to the [[Rotax Max]] Mini Max class and won the Rotax Max Challenge Belgium<ref>{{cite web|title=Rotax Max Challenge Belgium Minimax 2007|url=https://www.driverdb.com/championships/standings/rotax-max-challenge-belgium-minimax/2007/|work=DriverDB.com|access-date=27 January 2014|archive-date=24 August 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140824014222/http://www.driverdb.com/championships/standings/rotax-max-challenge-belgium-minimax/2007/|url-status=live}}</ref> and the Dutch Championship<ref>{{cite web|title=Dutch Championship Minimax 2007|url=https://www.driverdb.com/championships/dutch-championship-rotax-max-minimax/2007/|work=DriverDB.com|access-date=15 October 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230531002332/https://www.driverdb.com/championships/dutch-championship-rotax-max-minimax/2007/|archive-date=31 May 2023|url-status=live}}</ref> in that category. In 2008, racing in a [[CRG (kart manufacturer)|CRG]] kart entered by his father, Verstappen won the Belgian Cadet Championship,<ref>{{cite web|title=Belgian Championship&nbsp;– Cadet 2008|url=https://www.driverdb.com/championships/standings/belgian-championship---cadet/2008/|work=DriverDB.com|access-date=27 January 2014|archive-date=22 May 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210522154236/https://www.driverdb.com/championships/standings/belgian-championship---cadet/2008/|url-status=live}}</ref> as well as the Rotax Max Challenge Belgium<ref>{{cite web|title=Rotax Max Challenge Belgium Minimax 2008|url=https://www.driverdb.com/championships/standings/rotax-max-challenge-belgium-minimax/2008/|work=DriverDB.com|access-date=27 January 2014|archive-date=22 May 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210522154239/https://www.driverdb.com/championships/standings/rotax-max-challenge-belgium-minimax/2008/|url-status=live}}</ref> and Benelux Karting Series in Mini Max class.<ref>{{cite web|title=BNL Karting Series Minimax 2008|url=https://www.driverdb.com/championships/bnl-karting-series---minimax/2008/|work=DriverDB.com|access-date=15 October 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230531003941/https://www.driverdb.com/championships/bnl-karting-series---minimax/2008/|archive-date=31 May 2023|url-status=live}}</ref> In 2009, Verstappen joined Pex Racing, a CRG customer team. That year, he defended his titles in the Mini Max championships<ref>{{cite web|title=VAS Championship&nbsp;– Rotax Max Challenge Belgium Minimax 2009|url=https://www.driverdb.com/championships/standings/vas-championship---rotax-minimax/2009/|work=DriverDB.com|access-date=27 January 2014|archive-date=22 May 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210522154235/https://www.driverdb.com/championships/standings/vas-championship---rotax-minimax/2009/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=BNL Karting Series Mini Max 2009|url=https://www.driverdb.com/championships/bnl-karting-series---minimax/2009|work=DriverDB.com|access-date=15 October 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230530235643/https://www.driverdb.com/championships/bnl-karting-series---minimax/2009|archive-date=30 May 2023|url-status=live}}</ref> and won the Belgian KF5 Championship.<ref>{{cite web|title=Belgian Championship&nbsp;– KF5 2009|url=https://www.driverdb.com/championships/standings/belgian-championship---kf5/2009/|work=DriverDB.com|access-date=27 January 2014|archive-date=22 May 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210522154217/https://www.driverdb.com/championships/standings/belgian-championship---kf5/2009/|url-status=live}}</ref>

Verstappen was signed by CRG to race in their factory team and stepped up to international karting in 2010. At the [[KF3]] [[FIA Karting World Championship|World Cup]], Verstappen finished second to the more experienced [[Alexander Albon]] (who would eventually become his Formula One teammate at Red Bull Racing)<ref>{{cite web|title=CIK-FIA World Cup&nbsp;– KF3 2010|url=https://www.driverdb.com/championships/standings/world-cup---kf3/2010/|work=DriverDB.com|access-date=27 January 2014|archive-date=22 May 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210522154227/https://www.driverdb.com/championships/standings/world-cup---kf3/2010/|url-status=live}}</ref> but beat him at the [[2010 WSK Euro Series|WSK Euro Series]]<ref>{{cite web|title=WSK Euro Series – KF3 2010|url=https://www.driverdb.com/championships/wsk-euro-series---kf3/2010|work=DriverDB.com|access-date=15 October 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230531001112/https://www.driverdb.com/championships/wsk-euro-series---kf3/2010|archive-date=31 May 2023|url-status=live}}</ref>  and also won the WSK World Series, beating [[Robert Vișoiu]].<ref>{{cite web|title=WSK World Series&nbsp;– KF3 2010|url=https://www.driverdb.com/championships/standings/wsk-world-series---kf3/2010/|work=DriverDB.com|access-date=27 January 2014|archive-date=30 July 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140730035255/http://www.driverdb.com/championships/standings/wsk-world-series---kf3/2010/|url-status=live}}</ref> He finished fifth in the [[CIK-FIA Karting European Championship|European Championship]] and won the WSK Nations Cup<ref>{{cite web|title=WSK Nations Cup KF3 2010|url=https://www.driverdb.com/championships/wsk-nations-cup---kf3/2010|work=DriverDB.com|access-date=15 October 2023|archive-date=31 May 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230531003715/https://www.driverdb.com/championships/wsk-nations-cup---kf3/2010|url-status=live}}</ref> as well as the final of the Bridgestone Cup where during a 28 laps' race in the rain he beat [[Dennis Olsen (racing driver)|Dennis Olsen]] by over 11 seconds.<ref>{{cite web|title=Bridgestone Cup Final KF3 2010|url=https://news.verstappen.com/pdf/2010/2010-10-24_Bridgestone-Cup_Final_KF3.pdf|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231010192601/https://news.verstappen.com/pdf/2010/2010-10-24_Bridgestone-Cup_Final_KF3.pdf|archive-date=10 October 2023|url-status=live|access-date=16 October 2023}}</ref> In 2011, Verstappen won the [[2011 WSK Euro Series|WSK Euro Series]] ahead of [[Esteban Ocon]] in a [[Italian American Motor Engineering|Parilla]]-powered CRG kart.<ref>{{cite web|title=WSK Euro Series&nbsp;– KF3 2011|url=https://www.driverdb.com/championships/standings/wsk-euro-series---kf3/2011/|work=DriverDB.com|access-date=27 January 2014|archive-date=27 April 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140427010816/http://www.driverdb.com/championships/standings/wsk-euro-series---kf3/2011/|url-status=live}}</ref> However, it wasn't a successful year for him, as he finished 14th in the [[CIK-FIA Karting European Championship|European Championship]] and got taken out in the [[FIA Karting World Championship|World Cup]] by [[Charles Leclerc]]. 

In the following year, Verstappen joined the Intrepid Driver Program to race in the [[KF2]] and [[KZ2]] classes. He won the [[WSK Super Master Series|WSK Master Series]] in the KF2 class, beating the CRG driver Felice Tiene.<ref>{{cite web|title=WSK Master Series&nbsp;– KF2 2012|url=https://www.driverdb.com/championships/standings/wsk-master-series---kf2/2012/|work=DriverDB.com|access-date=27 January 2014|archive-date=22 May 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210522154309/https://www.driverdb.com/championships/standings/wsk-master-series---kf2/2012/|url-status=live}}</ref> Verstappen won the South Garda Winter Cup in the KF2 class, beating [[Dennis Olsen (racing driver)|Dennis Olsen]] and [[Antonio Fuoco]].<ref>{{cite web|title=17° Winter Cup&nbsp;– KF2 2012|url=https://www.driverdb.com/championships/standings/south-garda-winter-cup---kf2/2012/|work=DriverDB.com|access-date=27 January 2014|archive-date=22 May 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210522154314/https://www.driverdb.com/championships/standings/south-garda-winter-cup---kf2/2012/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=SKUSA SuperNationals XVI&nbsp;– KZ2 2012|url=https://www.driverdb.com/championships/standings/skusa-supernationals---kz2/2012/|work=DriverDB.com|access-date=27 January 2014|archive-date=22 May 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210522154319/https://www.driverdb.com/championships/standings/skusa-supernationals---kz2/2012/|url-status=live}}</ref> He finished sixth in the [[WSK Euro Series]].<ref>{{cite web|title=WSK Euro Series – KF2 2012|url=https://www.driverdb.com/championships/wsk-euro-series---kf2/2012|work=DriverDB.com|access-date=15 October 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230605105850/https://www.driverdb.com/championships/wsk-euro-series---kf2/2012|archive-date=5 June 2023|url-status=live}}</ref> He was the youngest driver taking part in the World Championship in [[KF1]] class and finished eight.<ref>{{cite web|title=World Championship– KF1 2012|url=https://www.driverdb.com/championships/world-championship-kf1/2012|work=DriverDB.com|access-date=15 October 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230531002806/https://www.driverdb.com/championships/world-championship-kf1/2012|archive-date=31 May 2023|url-status=live}}</ref>

In July 2012, it was announced that Verstappen would leave Intrepid. After a short stint with CRG-built [[Alex Zanardi|Zanardi]] karts, Verstappen returned to the factory CRG team.<ref>{{cite web|title=Max rijdt rest van seizoen op CRG kart met TM motor|url=http://www.verstappen.nl/?locatie=bericht&id=8038|work=Verstappen Info Page|access-date=27 January 2014|archive-date=5 February 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150205012637/http://www.verstappen.nl/?locatie=bericht&id=8038|url-status=live}}</ref> He finished second at the World Cup in the KF2 class<ref>{{cite web|title=World Cup– KF2 2012|url=https://www.driverdb.com/championships/world-cup---kf2/2012|work=DriverDB.com|access-date=15 October 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230605092022/https://www.driverdb.com/championships/world-cup---kf2/2012|archive-date=5 June 2023|url-status=live}}</ref> and competed at the SKUSA SuperNationals in the KZ2 class in a CRG, finishing 21st. 

In 2013, Verstappen completed a record-breaking season in karting. Aged 15, Verstappen won the South Garda Winter Cup in KF2<ref>{{cite web|title=South Garda Winter Cup – KF2 2013|url=https://www.driverdb.com/championships/south-garda-winter-cup---kf2/2013|work=DriverDB.com|access-date=9 October 2023|archive-date=10 October 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231010192604/https://www.driverdb.com/championships/south-garda-winter-cup---kf2/2013|url-status=live}}</ref> class and WSK Euro and Master Series in KZ class.<ref>{{cite web|title=WSK Euro Series – KZ1 2013|url=https://www.driverdb.com/championships/wsk-euro-series---kz1/2013|work=DriverDB.com|access-date=9 October 2023|archive-date=10 October 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231010192559/https://www.driverdb.com/championships/wsk-euro-series---kz1/2013|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=WSK Master Series – KZ2 2013|url=https://www.driverdb.com/championships/wsk-master-series---kz2/2013|work=DriverDB.com|access-date=9 October 2023|archive-date=8 October 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231008013540/https://www.driverdb.com/championships/wsk-master-series---kz2/2013|url-status=live}}</ref> He won two European Championships and a World Championship (the European and World KF and World KZ championships); an unprecedented feat in the history of the discipline.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Verstappen sets Karting world record|url=https://www.fiakarting.com/news/max-verstappen-an-exceptional-season-with-more-th|website=fiakarting.com|access-date=15 February 2022|archive-date=15 February 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220215021715/https://www.fiakarting.com/news/max-verstappen-an-exceptional-season-with-more-th|url-status=live}}</ref> Verstappen won the 2013 World KZ Championship at [[Varennes-sur-Allier]], France, beating Charles Leclerc<ref>{{cite web|title=World Championship – KZ 2013|url=https://www.driverdb.com/championships/world-championship-kz/2013|work=DriverDB.com|access-date=9 October 2023|archive-date=10 October 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231010192606/https://www.driverdb.com/championships/world-championship-kz/2013|url-status=live}}</ref> and becoming the youngest driver ever to win the KZ World Championship.<ref>{{Cite web|date=24 February 2014|title=Verstappen is KZ World Champion at 15!|url=https://www.fia.com/news/verstappen-kz-world-champion-15|access-date=20 January 2022|website=Federation Internationale de l'Automobile|archive-date=20 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220120232052/https://www.fia.com/news/verstappen-kz-world-champion-15|url-status=live}}</ref>

=== Florida Winter Series and Formula Three ===
