Verstappen's first experience in a racing car was at the [[Pembrey Circuit]] on 11 October 2013. He drove 160 laps in a [[Barazi-Epsilon]] FR2.0–10 [[Formula Renault]] car. The car was provided by Dutch team [[MP Motorsport]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Max Verstappen sensationeel in allereerste meters Formule Renault 2.0|url=http://www.racexpress.nl/formule-1/max-verstappen-sensationeel-in-allereerste-meters-formule-renault-2-0/n/53111|work=RaceXpress.nl|access-date=27 January 2014|archive-date=5 February 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150205021915/http://www.racexpress.nl/formule-1/max-verstappen-sensationeel-in-allereerste-meters-formule-renault-2-0/n/53111|url-status=live}}</ref> He tested for several Formula Renault 2.0 teams in 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gpupdate.net/nl/autosport-nieuws/303024/verstappen-max-al-net-zo-snel-als-ervaren-coureurs/|title=Verstappen: "Max al net zo snel als ervaren coureurs"|website=GPUpdate.net|access-date=2 September 2017|archive-date=2 September 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170902224144/http://www.gpupdate.net/nl/autosport-nieuws/303024/verstappen-max-al-net-zo-snel-als-ervaren-coureurs/|url-status=live}}</ref> In December 2013, Verstappen tested a [[Dallara]] F311 [[Formula Three|Formula 3]] car run by [[Motopark Academy]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Max Verstappen flies in Formula 3 test debut|url=https://www.autosport.com/fia-f3/news/max-verstappen-flies-in-formula-3-test-debut-4471773/4471773/|access-date=20 January 2022|website=Autosport|archive-date=20 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220120130449/https://www.autosport.com/fia-f3/news/max-verstappen-flies-in-formula-3-test-debut-4471773/4471773/|url-status=live}}</ref> An additional Formula Renault test followed in December at [[Circuito de Jerez]]. Driving for [[Josef Kaufmann Racing]], Verstappen went faster than Formula Renault regulars like [[Steijn Schothorst]] and [[Matt Parry]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Max op haar na snelste bij laatste FR 2.0 test van 2013|url=http://www.verstappen.nl/?locatie=bericht&id=8323|work=Verstappen Info Page|access-date=27 January 2014|archive-date=5 February 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150205012246/http://www.verstappen.nl/?locatie=bericht&id=8323|url-status=live}}</ref> At the [[Circuit Ricardo Tormo]] near [[Valencia]], Verstappen set a faster lap time than the more experienced driver [[Eddie Cheever III]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Max fenomenaal snel bij zijn eerste F3 test op Valencia|url=http://www.verstappen.nl/?locatie=bericht&id=8326|work=Verstappen Info Page|access-date=27 January 2014|archive-date=5 February 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150205012216/http://www.verstappen.nl/?locatie=bericht&id=8326|url-status=live}}</ref>

On 16 January 2014, it was announced Verstappen would make his racing debut in the non-championship [[Florida Winter Series]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Max maakt autosportdebuut in Florida Winter Series|url=http://www.verstappen.nl/?locatie=bericht&id=8336|work=Verstappen Info Page|access-date=27 January 2014|archive-date=5 February 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150205012639/http://www.verstappen.nl/?locatie=bericht&id=8336|url-status=live}}</ref> On 5 February, at the second race weekend, Verstappen won the race at [[Palm Beach International Raceway]] after he started from pole.<ref>{{cite web|title=Verstappen wint eerste autorace na regen en rode vlag|url=http://www.gpupdate.net/nl/autosport-nieuws/306301/verstappen-wint-eerste-autorace-na-rode-vlag|access-date=16 May 2016|archive-date=6 March 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160306004252/http://www.gpupdate.net/nl/autosport-nieuws/306301/verstappen-wint-eerste-autorace-na-rode-vlag/|url-status=live}}</ref> A few weeks later, Verstappen won his second race of the series at [[Homestead–Miami Speedway]] after beating [[Nicholas Latifi]] by 0.004 seconds.<ref>{{Citation|title=Max Verstappen Onboard FWS, Homestead race 3, 19/02/2014 – Max beats Latifi by 0.004s!|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rJQHa6nHV04|access-date=20 January 2022|archive-date=13 October 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221013203425/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rJQHa6nHV04|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Formule 1 nieuws – Lees het laatste nieuws over Formule 1|url=https://nl.motorsport.com/f1/news/|access-date=20 January 2022|website=nl.motorsport.com|language=nl|archive-date=18 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318043055/https://www.autosport.com/|url-status=live}}</ref> Following his single-seater debut in the inaugural Florida Winter Series, Verstappen drove in the [[FIA European Formula 3 Championship]] for [[Van Amersfoort Racing]].<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.fiaf3europe.com/en/news/Max-Verstappen-new-Red-Bull-Junior.html |title= Max Verstappen new part of the Red Bull Junior Team |publisher=Fédération Internationale de l'Automobile |access-date= 20 August 2014 |url-status=dead |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20150924012244/http://www.fiaf3europe.com/en/news/Max-Verstappen-new-Red-Bull-Junior.html |archive-date=24 September 2015 }}</ref> Aged 16, Verstappen scored a record six consecutive victories in the series, and a record ten victories in total, along with eight retirements and one DNS (did not start); placing third in the overall rankings.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Max Verstappen|url=https://www.redbull.com/gb-en/athlete/max-verstappen-bio|access-date=29 January 2022|publisher=Red Bull|language=en|archive-date=29 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220129030707/https://www.redbull.com/gb-en/athlete/max-verstappen-bio|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=2014 European F3 Championship|url=https://www.motorsportmagazine.com/database/championships/2014-european-f3-championship/|access-date=19 January 2022|work=Motor Sport Magazine|archive-date=22 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220122204809/https://www.motorsportmagazine.com/database/championships/2014-european-f3-championship/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Max Verstappen: what I learned in F3|url=https://www.redbull.com/gb-en/max-verstappen-interview-european-f3-review-2014|access-date=19 January 2022|publisher=Red Bull|archive-date=22 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220122204809/https://www.redbull.com/gb-en/max-verstappen-interview-european-f3-review-2014|url-status=live}}</ref>

== Formula One career ==
===Scuderia Toro Rosso (2014–2016)<!-- Please do not change 2014->2015. He was with Toro Rosso in 2014 even if he only acted as a third/test driver. Similary see Robert Kubica. -->===
During the first practice session at the [[2014 Japanese Grand Prix]], Verstappen replaced [[Jean-Éric Vergne]] as part of his preparation for a full-time seat at [[Scuderia Toro Rosso|Toro Rosso]] in the {{f1|2015}} season.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Benson|first=Andrew|date=29 September 2014|title=Max Verstappen: Teenager to drive in practice at Japanese Grand Prix|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/formula1/29408212|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160601084502/http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/formula1/29408212|archive-date=1 June 2016|access-date=23 July 2016|publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref> Aged 17 years and three days, Verstappen was the youngest person in history to participate in a Formula One race weekend.<ref>{{Cite web |date=24 July 2016 |title=Japanese Grand Prix 2014: History-maker Max Verstappen flies like the wind as typhoon zooms closer |url=http://www.independent.co.uk/sport/motor-racing/japanese-grand-prix-2014-history-maker-max-verstappen-flies-like-the-wind-as-typhoon-zooms-closer-9773924.html |access-date=22 January 2022 |website=[[The Independent]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160724110219/http://www.independent.co.uk/sport/motor-racing/japanese-grand-prix-2014-history-maker-max-verstappen-flies-like-the-wind-as-typhoon-zooms-closer-9773924.html |archive-date=24 July 2016 |url-status=dead}}</ref> In August 2014, Verstappen joined the [[Red Bull Junior Team]] after testing a Formula Renault 3.5 car. He also considered an offer from [[Mercedes-Benz in Formula One|Mercedes]] to join their [[Mercedes Junior Team|driver development programme]].<ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.nu.nl/sport/3850611/max-verstappen-per-direct-opgenomen-in-opleiding-red-bull.html|title= Max Verstappen per direct opgenomen in opleiding Red Bull|date= 12 August 2014|work= verstappen.nl|access-date= 18 August 2014|publisher= Nu.nl|archive-date= 22 May 2021|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20210522154400/https://www.nu.nl/sport/3850611/max-verstappen-per-direct-opgenomen-in-opleiding-red-bull.html|url-status= live}}</ref>

[[File:Max Verstappen 2015 Malaysia Q2.jpg|thumb|Verstappen driving for Scuderia Toro Rosso at the 2015 Malaysian Grand Prix]]
Verstappen became the [[List of Formula One driver records#Youngest drivers to start a race|youngest driver to start a World Championship race]] through joining Toro Rosso's race drivers’ line-up with [[Carlos Sainz Jr.|Carlos Sainz]] as his teammate, in his Grand Prix debut as a full-time driver at the [[2015 Australian Grand Prix]] at the age of {{Age in years and days|1997|9|30|2015|3|15}}{{Emdash}}breaking [[Jaime Alguersuari]]'s existing record by almost two years.<ref>{{cite news|title=Max Verstappen to race with Toro Rosso F1 team in 2015|work=Autosport|url=http://www.autosport.com/news/report.php/id/115435|date=18 August 2014|access-date=18 August 2014|archive-date=1 July 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170701130917/http://www.autosport.com/news/report.php/id/115435|url-status=live}}</ref> In this first race, Verstappen ran in points-scoring positions until he was forced to retire due to an engine failure.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.autosport.com/news/report.php/id/118069|title=Lewis Hamilton beats Nico Rosberg to win|first=Lawrence|last=Barretto|work=[[Autosport]]|date=15 March 2015|access-date=29 March 2015|archive-date=16 March 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150316231343/http://www.autosport.com/news/report.php/id/118069|url-status=live}}</ref> However, at the subsequent race in [[2015 Malaysian Grand Prix|Malaysia]], Verstappen qualified sixth and finished the race in seventh place, scoring his first Formula One points aged {{Age in years and days|1997|9|30|2015|3|29}}, breaking the record of the then-[[List of Formula One driver records#Youngest drivers to score points|youngest driver to score World Championship points]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/motorsport/formulaone/sebastian-vettel/11502398/Malaysian-GP-2015-Sebastian-Vettel-picks-up-surprise-win-for-Ferrari-to-blow-world-title-wide-open.html |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220110/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/motorsport/formulaone/sebastian-vettel/11502398/Malaysian-GP-2015-Sebastian-Vettel-picks-up-surprise-win-for-Ferrari-to-blow-world-title-wide-open.html |archive-date=10 January 2022 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live|title=Sebastian Vettel picks up surprise win for Ferrari to blow world title wide open|first=Daniel|last=Johnson|work=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|date=29 March 2015|access-date=29 March 2015|quote=Max Verstappen took seventh to become the youngest points scorer in F1 history, at 17 years and 180 days.}}{{cbignore}}</ref>

At the [[2015 Monaco Grand Prix]], Verstappen was involved in a high-speed collision with [[Romain Grosjean]], after clipping the back of Grosjean's [[Lotus F1|Lotus]] on the approach to the tight first corner, Sainte Devote, and crashed into the barriers at high speed.<ref>{{Citation|title=5 Crazy Onboards {{!}} Monaco Grand Prix|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sMde0gU-KhQ|access-date=20 January 2022|archive-date=20 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220120132014/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sMde0gU-KhQ|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Monaco GP: Max Verstappen penalised for crash with Romain Grosjean|url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/monaco-gp-max-verstappen-penalised-for-crash-with-romain-grosjean-5006608/5006608/|access-date=20 January 2022|website=Autosport|date=24 May 2015 |archive-date=17 December 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211217052426/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/monaco-gp-max-verstappen-penalised-for-crash-with-romain-grosjean-5006608/5006608/|url-status=live}}</ref> Verstappen was given a five-place grid penalty for causing the accident, and was branded "dangerous" by [[Williams Grand Prix Engineering|Williams]] driver [[Felipe Massa]].<ref>William Esler, "[http://www.skysports.com/f1/news/31381/9875227/max-verstappen-hits-back-at-felipe-massa-of-monaco-crash-criticism Max Verstappen hits back at Felipe Massa over Monaco crash criticism] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160611182531/http://www.skysports.com/f1/news/31381/9875227/max-verstappen-hits-back-at-felipe-massa-of-monaco-crash-criticism |date=11 June 2016 }}", [[Sky Sports]], 2015.</ref>

Verstappen continued to regularly finish in the points as well as achieving his best finish of the 2015 season in [[2015 Hungarian Grand Prix|Hungary]] by finishing fourth,<ref>{{Cite web|title=9 things we learned from the Hungarian Grand Prix|url=https://www.redbull.com/gb-en/2015-hungarian-grand-prix-f1-report|access-date=19 January 2022|publisher=Red Bull|archive-date=10 March 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220310191111/https://www.redbull.com/gb-en/2015-hungarian-grand-prix-f1-report|url-status=live}}</ref> and equalled this result at the [[2015 United States Grand Prix|United States Grand Prix]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Hamilton seals 2015 title with thrilling Austin win|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/headlines/2015/10/hamilton-seals-2015-title-with-thrilling-austin-win.html|access-date=19 January 2022|publisher=Formula One|archive-date=25 December 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211225175054/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/headlines/2015/10/hamilton-seals-2015-title-with-thrilling-austin-win.html|url-status=live}}</ref> At the end of the season, Verstappen received three awards at the [[FIA Prize Giving Ceremony]], for "Rookie of the Year", "Personality of the Year" and "Action of the Year", for his overtake on [[Felipe Nasr]] on the outside of the Blanchimont corner at the [[2015 Belgian Grand Prix|Belgian Grand Prix]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Galloway|first1=James|title=Lewis Hamilton & Mercedes officially crowned 2015 world champions|url=http://www.skysports.com/f1/news/24181/10087594/lewis-hamilton-mercedes-officially-crowned-2015-world-champions|publisher=Sky Sports|access-date=5 December 2015|date=5 December 2015|archive-date=5 December 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151205171818/http://www.skysports.com/f1/news/24181/10087594/lewis-hamilton-mercedes-officially-crowned-2015-world-champions|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|title=Top 10 Moments of Max Verstappen Magic in F1|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=B4pF4bMwYYI|access-date=19 January 2022|archive-date=19 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220119223659/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=B4pF4bMwYYI|url-status=live}}</ref>

[[File:Verstappen Bahrain 2016.jpg|alt=|thumb|Verstappen at the [[2016 Bahrain Grand Prix]]]]
Verstappen began the 2016 season at Toro Rosso, again alongside Sainz.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Max Verstappen and Carlos Sainz to continue for Toro Rosso in 2016|url=https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12471/10084883/toro-rosso-have-confirmed-that-max-verstappen-and-carlos-sainz-will-race-in-2016|access-date=19 January 2022|publisher=Sky Sports|archive-date=19 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220119221049/https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12471/10084883/toro-rosso-have-confirmed-that-max-verstappen-and-carlos-sainz-will-race-in-2016|url-status=live}}</ref> Verstappen qualified fifth for the opening race of the season in [[2016 Australian Grand Prix|Australia]], but during the race made several radio calls to his team due to frustration at being behind Sainz on track before Verstappen's Toro Rosso came into contact with his teammate's car whilst attempting to pass him with three laps to go, and he eventually finished tenth.<ref>"[https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/formula1/35854819 Max Verstappen: Australian GP shows moody side of Toro Rosso teenager] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160323010100/http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/formula1/35854819 |date=23 March 2016 }}", [[BBC Sport]], 2016.</ref> Verstappen enjoyed a more successful weekend at the following race in [[2016 Bahrain Grand Prix|Bahrain]], finishing sixth to score Toro Rosso's first-ever points at the Sakhir circuit.<ref>"[http://www.gpupdate.net/en/f1-news/337624/verstappen-scores-str-s-first-bahrain-points/ Verstappen scores STR's first Bahrain points] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160511232826/http://www.gpupdate.net/en/f1-news/337624/verstappen-scores-str-s-first-bahrain-points/ |date=11 May 2016 }}", ''GP Update'', 2016.</ref>

===Red Bull (2016–present)===
====2016 season====
[[File:Verstappen Spain 2016.jpg|thumb|Verstappen celebrating victory at the [[2016 Spanish Grand Prix]], in his first race for the Red Bull Racing team]]

On 5 May 2016, following the {{F1GP|2016|Russian}}, Red Bull Racing announced that Verstappen would be replacing Daniil Kvyat from the [[2016 Spanish Grand Prix|Spanish Grand Prix]] onwards, with Kvyat returning to Toro Rosso.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Red Bull replace Kvyat with Verstappen|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/headlines/2016/5/red-bull-replace-kvyat-with-verstappen.html|access-date=19 January 2022|publisher=Formula One|archive-date=20 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220120221159/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/headlines/2016/5/red-bull-replace-kvyat-with-verstappen.html|url-status=live}}</ref> According to Red Bull Team Principal [[Christian Horner]], "Max has proven to be an outstanding young talent. His performance at Toro Rosso has been impressive so far and we are pleased to give him the opportunity to drive for Red Bull Racing."<ref name="RBR Swap">{{cite news|url=http://www.redbullracing.com/article/new-line-spain|title=New line-up for Spain|work=RedBullRacing.com|date=5 May 2016|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160508080016/http://www.redbullracing.com/article/new-line-spain|archive-date=8 May 2016}}</ref> After qualifying fourth for the Spanish Grand Prix,<ref name="Verstappen 4th in Qualifying">{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/live/formula1/35946953|title=Hamilton takes pole in Spain|publisher=BBC Sport|date=14 May 2016|access-date=12 February 2018|archive-date=20 December 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181220042109/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/live/formula1/35946953|url-status=live}}</ref> Verstappen rose to second behind teammate [[Daniel Ricciardo]] on the opening lap after Mercedes teammates [[Lewis Hamilton]] and [[Nico Rosberg]] crashed out of the race.<ref>{{Cite web|title=WATCH: Mercedes collision puts Hamilton and Rosberg out on lap 1|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/headlines/2016/5/mercedes-collision-puts-hamilton-and-rosberg-out-on-lap-one.html|access-date=19 January 2022|publisher=Formula One|archive-date=24 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220124222604/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/headlines/2016/5/mercedes-collision-puts-hamilton-and-rosberg-out-on-lap-one.html|url-status=live}}</ref> Verstappen took the race lead as he was placed on a two-stop rather than the same three-stop strategy as Ricciardo, and he held off [[Scuderia Ferrari|Ferrari]]'s [[Kimi Räikkönen]] in the later stages of the race to take his first Formula One victory.<ref>{{Citation|title=2016 Spanish Grand Prix: Race Highlights|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3B3-C914d_c|access-date=19 January 2022|archive-date=21 April 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220421042514/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3B3-C914d_c|url-status=live}}</ref> By doing so he displaced [[Sebastian Vettel]] as the youngest driver ever to win a Formula One Grand Prix at the age of 18 years and 228 days.<ref name=":0" />

In his first eight races with Red Bull, he achieved six top-five finishes, including four podiums.<ref name="Standings">{{cite web|url=https://www.statsf1.com/en/max-verstappen/grand-prix.aspx|title=Max Verstappen – Grands Prix|access-date=13 June 2022|website=StatsF1|archive-date=13 June 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220613195714/https://www.statsf1.com/en/max-verstappen/grand-prix.aspx|url-status=live}}</ref>

During the [[2016 Belgian Grand Prix|Belgian Grand Prix]], Verstappen collided with Räikkönen at the first corner, pushed Vettel, Räikkönen and Pérez wide at ''Les Combes'', and aggressively blocked Räikkönen on the Kemmel straight.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/formula1/37226080|title=Formula 1: Max Verstappen gets under the skin of top drivers|publisher=BBC Sport|date=31 August 2016|access-date=4 November 2016|archive-date=13 November 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161113170546/http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/formula1/37226080|url-status=live}}</ref> Verstappen was criticised for his driving, with Räikkönen saying that he "was going to cause a huge accident sooner or later." Christian Horner noted that the driving was "on the edge", and that Verstappen will "look at it and learn for future races."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.co.uk/f1/story/_/id/17413337/christian-horner-says-max-verstappen-learn-belgium|title=Horner: Verstappen will learn from Belgium|publisher=ESPN|date=29 August 2016|access-date=4 November 2016|archive-date=7 November 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161107083945/http://www.espn.co.uk/f1/story/_/id/17413337/christian-horner-says-max-verstappen-learn-belgium|url-status=live}}</ref> In September, Formula One director [[Charlie Whiting]] called in Verstappen for a discussion, and later gave him a 'gentle warning' due to his aggressive driving.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/formula1/37258313|title=Italian GP: Max Verstappen given 'gentle warning' by FIA|publisher=BBC Sport|date=2 September 2016|access-date=4 November 2016|archive-date=6 September 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160906224118/http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/formula1/37258313|url-status=live}}</ref> However, in October, drivers' concerns about Verstappen's defensive tactics led the FIA to disallow moving under braking.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/formula1/37741994|title=Formula 1 outlaws moving under braking after protests over Max Verstappen|publisher=BBC Sport|date=22 October 2016|access-date=12 February 2018|archive-date=2 September 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170902235036/http://www.bbc.com/sport/formula1/37741994|url-status=live}}</ref>

At the [[2016 Brazilian Grand Prix]], Verstappen qualified fourth.<ref>{{cite web|title=Formula 1 Grande Premio do Brasil 2016 – Qualifying |url=http://www.formula1.com/en/results.html/2016/races/956/brazil/qualifying.html |publisher=Formula One |access-date=17 November 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161117112850/http://www.formula1.com/en/results.html/2016/races/956/brazil/qualifying.html |archive-date=17 November 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref> In a rain affected race, he almost hit the barrier after he slid on the main straight due to a loss of traction, causing [[oversteer]].<ref>{{Citation|title=Verstappen's Amazing Save in Brazil {{!}} F1 is...Heart-in-Mouth|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wQCeQKQ7_vI|access-date=19 January 2022|archive-date=10 March 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220310040858/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wQCeQKQ7_vI|url-status=live}}</ref> After an additional tyre change from intermediates back to rain tyres, he ran in 16th place with just 15 laps remaining. Verstappen then made several overtakes in quick succession during the closing laps to eventually finish on the podium in third place.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Galloway |first1=James |title=Max Verstappen stole the show in Brazil GP, says Mercedes' Toto Wolff |url=http://www.skysports.com/f1/news/31381/10657138/max-verstappen-stole-the-show-in-brazil-gp-says-mercedes-toto-wolff |publisher=Sky Sports |access-date=17 November 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161117112959/http://www.skysports.com/f1/news/31381/10657138/max-verstappen-stole-the-show-in-brazil-gp-says-mercedes-toto-wolff |archive-date=17 November 2016 |date=14 November 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref> He received considerable praise for his performance: rival team Mercedes' team principal, [[Toto Wolff]], labelled it "The Verstappen Show", and described Verstappen's drive as "physics..being redefined".<ref>{{cite web|last1=Gill |first1=Pete |last2=Esler |first2=William |title=Max Verstappen's Brazilian GP drive hailed as 'one of the best ever in F1' |url=http://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12040/10656712/max-verstappens-brazilian-gp-drive-hailed-as-one-of-the-best-ever-in-f1 |publisher=Sky Sports |access-date=17 November 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161117113003/http://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12040/10656712/max-verstappens-brazilian-gp-drive-hailed-as-one-of-the-best-ever-in-f1 |archive-date=17 November 2016 |date=14 November 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{Citation|title=Max Verstappen's Masterclass {{!}} 2016 Brazilian Grand Prix|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JO3q69x2sXA|access-date=22 January 2022|archive-date=22 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220122133251/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JO3q69x2sXA|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Verstappen's Brazil drive earns Senna/Schumacher comparisons|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/headlines/2016/11/f1-verstappen-brazil-gp-senna-schumacher-comparisons.html|access-date=22 January 2022|publisher=Formula One|archive-date=22 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220122133250/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/headlines/2016/11/f1-verstappen-brazil-gp-senna-schumacher-comparisons.html|url-status=live}}</ref> However, Verstappen came under criticism from four-time world champion Sebastian Vettel, who stated that Verstappen had pushed him off the track at the Junção corner late in the race. The race stewards did not share Vettel's view and decided that no reprimand was warranted.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Edmondson |first1=Laurence |title=Vettel: Verstappen move was 'not correct' |url=http://www.espn.co.uk/f1/story/_/id/18041493/max-verstappen-move-was-not-correct |publisher=ESPN |access-date=17 November 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161117113518/http://www.espn.co.uk/f1/story/_/id/18041493/max-verstappen-move-was-not-correct |archive-date=17 November 2016 |date=14 November 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref>

====2017 season====
[[File:2017 British Grand Prix (35127086003).jpg|thumb|right|Verstappen at the [[2017 British Grand Prix]]]]
During the first 14 races of the 2017 season, Verstappen suffered seven retirements, four due to mechanical issues,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/formula1/41068214|title=Max Verstappen: Red Bull's reliability unacceptable|publisher=BBC Sport|date=27 August 2017|access-date=12 February 2018|archive-date=30 August 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170830010414/http://www.bbc.com/sport/formula1/41068214|url-status=live}}</ref> and three due to first lap collisions in [[2017 Spanish Grand Prix|Spain]], [[2017 Austrian Grand Prix|Austria]] and [[2017 Singapore Grand Prix|Singapore]].<ref>[http://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/10877127/spanish-gp-valtteri-bottas-triggers-max-verstappen-kimi-raikkonen-crash Spanish GP: Valtteri Bottas triggers Max Verstappen-Kimi Raikkonen crash] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170628083609/http://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/10877127/spanish-gp-valtteri-bottas-triggers-max-verstappen-kimi-raikkonen-crash |date=28 June 2017 }} – James Galloway and Emily McNally, Sky Sports, 14 May 2017</ref> Of the races he finished, however, he claimed a third place in [[2017 Chinese Grand Prix|China]], and in another five races he finished fourth or fifth.<ref name="Standings"/>

From the [[2017 Malaysian Grand Prix|Malaysian Grand Prix]] onward, Verstappen enjoyed a surge of success. He won his second Formula One race at the 2017 Malaysian Grand Prix, a day after his 20th birthday, passing then three-time champion Lewis Hamilton for the lead in the early stages of the race.<ref>{{Cite web|date=1 October 2017|title=Max Verstappen beats Lewis Hamilton to win F1's Malaysian Grand Prix|url=http://www.theguardian.com/sport/2017/oct/01/max-verstappen-lewis-hamilton-f1-malaysian-grand-prix-race-report-formula-one|access-date=19 January 2022|website=The Guardian|archive-date=15 December 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211215041014/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2017/oct/01/max-verstappen-lewis-hamilton-f1-malaysian-grand-prix-race-report-formula-one|url-status=live}}</ref> He finished second in the following [[2017 Japanese Grand Prix|race in Japan]].<ref>{{cite web|title=2017 Formula 1 Japanese Grand Prix – Race Result|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/results.html/2017/races/974/japan/race-result.html|publisher=Formula One|access-date=24 October 2017|archive-date=7 October 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171007170355/https://www.formula1.com/en/results.html/2017/races/974/japan/race-result.html|url-status=live}}</ref> He then finished third at the [[2017 United States Grand Prix|United States]] Grand Prix, but was classified fourth after his final lap overtake on Kimi Räikkönen was deemed illegal.<ref>{{cite web|title=2017 Formula 1 United States Grand Prix – Race Result|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/results.html/2017/races/975/united-states.html|publisher=Formula One|access-date=24 October 2017|archive-date=22 October 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171022215609/https://www.formula1.com/en/results.html/2017/races/975/united-states.html|url-status=live}}</ref> He won his third Formula One race at the [[2017 Mexican Grand Prix|Mexican Grand Prix]], after passing [[Sebastian Vettel]] on the opening lap.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/results.html/2017/races/976/mexico.html|title=Formula 1 Gran Premio de México 2017 – Race Result|publisher=Formula One|access-date=29 October 2017|archive-date=27 October 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171027235005/https://www.formula1.com/en/results.html/2017/races/976/mexico.html|url-status=live}}</ref>

====2018 season====
[[File:FIA F1 Austria 2018 Nr. 33 Verstappen.jpg|thumb|Verstappen at the [[2018 Austrian Grand Prix]]]]
In the first six races of the season, Verstappen had been involved in at least one incident in each race. In [[2018 Australian Grand Prix|Australia]], he qualified fourth but fell behind [[Kevin Magnussen]] at the start.<ref>{{Cite web|title=F1 Results – 2018 Australian Grand Prix|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/formula1/2018/australian-grand-prix/results/qualifying|access-date=19 January 2022|publisher=BBC Sport|archive-date=19 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220119232004/https://www.bbc.com/sport/formula1/2018/australian-grand-prix/results/qualifying|url-status=live}}</ref> In his attempts to retake the position he ran wide multiple times and damaged his car, with a spin causing him to fall further down the order. He recovered to eventually finish the race in sixth place.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/135028/early-damage-a-factor-in-verstappen-spin|title=Early damage a factor in Max Verstappen's Australian GP spin|last1=Mitchell|first1=Scott|date=25 March 2018|work=[[Autosport]]|publisher=[[Motorsport Network]]|last2=Cozens|first2=Jack|access-date=30 May 2018|archive-date=2 July 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200702202827/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/135028/early-damage-a-factor-in-verstappen-spin|url-status=live}}</ref> At the next race in [[2018 Bahrain Grand Prix|Bahrain]], he crashed during qualifying and started in 15th place.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.eurosport.co.uk/formula-1/bahrain-grand-prix/2018/verstappen-s-right-foot-caused-bahrain-crash_sto6711276/story.shtml|title=Verstappen's right foot caused Bahrain crash|date=13 April 2018|publisher=Eurosport UK|access-date=30 May 2018|archive-date=2 July 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200702202828/https://www.eurosport.com/geoblocking.shtml|url-status=live}}</ref> He had a productive first lap after which he found himself in the points while challenging Lewis Hamilton. He attempted an overtake on the reigning World Champion at the start of lap two, but collided with the Mercedes driver and suffered a puncture that ultimately led to suspension damage, forcing him out of the race.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12514/11316602/bahrain-gp-sebastian-vettel-holds-off-valtteri-bottas-for-victory|title=Bahrain GP: Sebastian Vettel holds off Valtteri Bottas for victory|last=Gill|first=Pete|date=9 April 2018|publisher=Sky Sports F1|access-date=30 May 2018|archive-date=13 June 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180613092534/http://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12514/11316602/bahrain-gp-sebastian-vettel-holds-off-valtteri-bottas-for-victory|url-status=live}}</ref>

At the next race in [[2018 Chinese Grand Prix|China]], Verstappen qualified fifth and had moved up to third at the end of the first lap.<ref>{{Citation|title=2018 Chinese Grand Prix: Race Highlights|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uiub1DnUnkg|access-date=19 January 2022|archive-date=19 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220119232004/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uiub1DnUnkg|url-status=live}}</ref> Both Red Bull drivers pitted for fresh tyres during a safety car which left them with a tyre advantage over the front-runners ahead. In an overtake attempt on [[Sebastian Vettel]] for third place, Verstappen collided with the championship leader, causing him to fall to eighth and receive a 10-second penalty.<ref>{{Citation|title=Verstappen Runs into Vettel {{!}} 2018 Chinese Grand Prix|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GR3Ls5tcp5A|access-date=19 January 2022|archive-date=13 October 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221013203419/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GR3Ls5tcp5A|url-status=live}}</ref> He recovered to fourth place, with his penalty causing him to be classified fifth. Teammate Ricciardo went on to win the race.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/135405/ricciardo-wins-vettel-and-verstappen-collide|title=Chinese Grand Prix: Ricciardo wins, Verstappen and Vettel collide|last=Mitchell|first=Scott|date=15 April 2018|work=[[Autosport]]|publisher=[[Motorsport Network]]|access-date=30 May 2018|archive-date=16 April 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180416043910/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/135405/ricciardo-wins-vettel-and-verstappen-collide|url-status=live}}</ref> In [[2018 Azerbaijan Grand Prix|Azerbaijan]], Verstappen was embroiled in a race-long battle with Ricciardo for fourth place. After numerous position changes between the two teammates during the race, Ricciardo ran into the back of Verstappen during an overtake attempt from which the Dutchman aggressively defended, causing the retirement of both cars.<ref>{{Citation|title=All The Angles: Ricciardo and Verstappen Crash {{!}} 2018 Azerbaijan Grand Prix|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=36YFQTFzZwU|access-date=19 January 2022|archive-date=13 October 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221013203426/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=36YFQTFzZwU|url-status=live}}</ref> Both drivers were blamed by the team and reprimanded by the stewards.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/11352821/max-verstappen-daniel-ricciardo-reprimanded-for-all-red-bull-azerbaijan-gp-crash|title=Max Verstappen, Daniel Ricciardo reprimanded for all-Red Bull Azerbaijan GP crash|last=Galloway|first=James|date=30 April 2018|publisher=[[Sky Sports F1]]|access-date=30 May 2018|archive-date=11 June 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180611131807/http://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/11352821/max-verstappen-daniel-ricciardo-reprimanded-for-all-red-bull-azerbaijan-gp-crash|url-status=live}}</ref> Verstappen bounced back in [[2018 Spanish Grand Prix|Spain]] with his first podium of the season by finishing third behind the Mercedes drivers, holding off [[Sebastian Vettel]]. However, the race was also not without incident as he had run into the back of [[Lance Stroll]] during the virtual safety car period, causing minor front wing damage.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/features/2018/5/winners-and-losers--spanish-grand-prix-edition.html|title=Winners and Losers – Spanish Grand Prix edition|date=14 May 2018|publisher=Formula One|access-date=30 May 2018|archive-date=14 May 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180514153208/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/features/2018/5/winners-and-losers--spanish-grand-prix-edition.html|url-status=live}}</ref>

In [[2018 Monaco Grand Prix|Monaco]], Verstappen made another error and crashed near the end of the third free practice session in an incident which closely resembled a crash he had at the same spot [[2016 Monaco Grand Prix#Qualifying|two years earlier]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/136314/ricciardo-fastest-as-verstappen-crashes-in-fp3|title=Monaco GP F1 practice: Ricciardo fastest as Verstappen crashes in FP3|last=Mitchell|first=Scott|date=26 May 2018|work=[[Autosport]]|publisher=[[Motorsport Network]]|access-date=30 May 2018|archive-date=16 October 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181016081329/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/136314/ricciardo-fastest-as-verstappen-crashes-in-fp3|url-status=live}}</ref> His team could not repair his car in time for qualifying and Verstappen had to start the race from the back of the grid.<ref name=":1">{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/formula1/44267114|title=Monaco Grand Prix: Max Verstappen crash 'unnecessary', says Red Bull's Helmut Marko|last=Benson|first=Andrew|date=26 May 2018|publisher=BBC Sport|access-date=30 May 2018|archive-date=14 June 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180614165357/https://www.bbc.com/sport/formula1/44267114|url-status=live}}</ref> Verstappen did not compete and did not set a lap time in qualifying, therefore teammate Ricciardo pressed home Red Bull's advantage at the track by taking [[pole position]] and the race win. Verstappen managed to salvage two points by finishing ninth place, overtaking six cars on track.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/136339/ricciardo-wins-monaco-gp-despite-car-problem|title=Monaco Grand Prix: Daniel Ricciardo wins despite car problem|last=Mitchell|first=Scott|date=27 May 2018|work=[[Autosport]]|publisher=[[Motorsport Network]]|access-date=30 May 2018|archive-date=16 October 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181016032724/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/136339/ricciardo-wins-monaco-gp-despite-car-problem|url-status=live}}</ref> Team principal Christian Horner commented on Verstappen's start of the season, saying he "needed to stop making these mistakes" and that he could "learn from his teammate", while [[Helmut Marko]], head of driver development at Red Bull, said that Verstappen was "too impatient".<ref name=":1" /> Verstappen now lay in sixth place in the championship with 35 points, only three points ahead of [[Fernando Alonso]] in the McLaren, and 37 points behind his teammate in third, who had taken two wins in the first six races.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Woolcock|first=Adam|date=15 April 2018|title=F1 2018: Daniel Ricciardo wins Chinese Grand Prix – as it happened|work=The Guardian|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/live/2018/apr/15/formula-one-2018-chinese-grand-prix-live|access-date=19 January 2022|issn=0261-3077|archive-date=22 April 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180422223322/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/live/2018/apr/15/formula-one-2018-chinese-grand-prix-live|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=F1 REWIND: Watch Daniel Ricciardo's brilliant 2018 Monaco Grand Prix win|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.watch-live-join-our-stream-of-ricciardos-brilliant-2018-monaco-grand-prix.13UtM2BlgsaIn5QzBe6B4l.html|access-date=19 January 2022|publisher=Formula One|archive-date=10 March 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220310074110/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.watch-live-join-our-stream-of-ricciardos-brilliant-2018-monaco-grand-prix.13UtM2BlgsaIn5QzBe6B4l.html|url-status=live}}</ref>

In [[2018 Canadian Grand Prix|Canada]], Verstappen topped all three practice sessions and qualified third, two-tenths off Sebastian Vettel in pole position.<ref>{{Cite web|title=F1 Results – 2018 Canadian Grand Prix|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/formula1/2018/canadian-grand-prix/results/qualifying|access-date=19 January 2022|publisher=BBC Sport|archive-date=19 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220119232005/https://www.bbc.com/sport/formula1/2018/canadian-grand-prix/results/qualifying|url-status=live}}</ref> He eventually finished third and set the fastest lap of the race.<ref>{{Cite web|date=10 June 2018|title=Sebastian Vettel wins Canadian Grand Prix despite chequered flag mix-up|url=http://www.theguardian.com/sport/2018/jun/10/sebastian-vettel-wins-canadian-grand-prix-f1-championship-lewis-hamilton|access-date=19 January 2022|website=The Guardian|archive-date=16 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220116233202/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2018/jun/10/sebastian-vettel-wins-canadian-grand-prix-f1-championship-lewis-hamilton|url-status=live}}</ref> The following race in [[2018 French Grand Prix|France]] brought him second place.<ref>{{Cite web|title=F1 Results – 2018 French Grand Prix|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/formula1/2018/french-grand-prix/results|access-date=19 January 2022|publisher=BBC Sport|archive-date=19 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220119232007/https://www.bbc.com/sport/formula1/2018/french-grand-prix/results|url-status=live}}</ref> In [[2018 Austrian Grand Prix|Austria]]—Red Bull's home track, he started fourth on the grid, passed Kimi Räikkönen before taking advantage of retirement from [[Valtteri Bottas]] and a botched pit-stop strategy by Lewis Hamilton, who later had to retire from fourth place, to claim the fourth race victory of his career.<ref>{{Citation|title=2018 Austrian Grand Prix: Race Highlights|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JNmfS9PSeYg|access-date=19 January 2022|archive-date=19 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220119232005/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JNmfS9PSeYg|url-status=live}}</ref> In [[2018 British Grand Prix|Britain]], Verstappen was plagued by issues, finishing the first practice session early due to a gearbox problem and crashing in the second practice session before retiring from the race due to a brake problem.<ref>{{Cite web|date=8 July 2018|title=F1: The reason Max Verstappen spun then retired from the British GP|url=https://www.foxsports.com.au/motorsport/formula-one/f1-the-reason-max-verstappen-spun-then-retired-from-the-british-gp/news-story/bf90c9db2308a1b68936d240a7549c95|access-date=19 January 2022|work=Fox Sports|archive-date=19 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220119232005/https://www.foxsports.com.au/motorsport/formula-one/f1-the-reason-max-verstappen-spun-then-retired-from-the-british-gp/news-story/bf90c9db2308a1b68936d240a7549c95|url-status=live}}</ref> He would then finish fourth in [[2018 German Grand Prix|Germany]] after strategy errors let a recovering Hamilton get past him as he went on to win the race.<ref>{{Citation|title=2018 German Grand Prix: Race Highlights|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gp-i8vtgzJE|access-date=19 January 2022|archive-date=13 October 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221013203408/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gp-i8vtgzJE|url-status=live}}</ref> Verstappen ended the first half of the season with a retirement in [[2018 Hungarian Grand Prix|Hungary]] and was narrowly behind his teammate in the championship due to his own recent resurgence and Ricciardo's unreliability.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Ricciardo: 'Weird' reliability inexplicable|url=https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/ricciardo-weird-reliability-inexplicable/3202443/|access-date=19 January 2022|website=Motorsport.com|date=26 October 2018 |archive-date=24 April 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220424225311/https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/ricciardo-weird-reliability-inexplicable/3202443/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=RACE: Verstappen retires early in Hungary|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/video.race-verstappen-retires-early-in-hungary.6060943592001.html|access-date=19 January 2022|publisher=Formula One|archive-date=10 March 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220310022859/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/video.race-verstappen-retires-early-in-hungary.6060943592001.html|url-status=live}}</ref>

Verstappen enjoyed a very strong second half of the season, achieving podium finishes in [[2018 Belgian Grand Prix|Belgium]], [[2018 Singapore Grand Prix|Singapore]], [[2018 Japanese Grand Prix|Japan]] and the [[2018 United States Grand Prix|United States]], the latter of which he achieved second place having started from 18th on the grid due to a suspension failure in qualifying.<ref>{{Citation|title=2018 United States Grand Prix: Race Highlights|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PNwPpqaLE60|access-date=19 January 2022|archive-date=19 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220119232524/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PNwPpqaLE60|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Standings|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/results.html|access-date=19 January 2022|website=Formula 1 – The Official F1 Website|archive-date=28 October 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141028202800/http://www.formula1.com/results/driver/2001/40.html|url-status=live}}</ref> Following the qualifying session at the [[2018 Mexican Grand Prix|Mexican Grand Prix]], Verstappen revealed that a mechanical problem with his Red Bull under braking cost him any chance of becoming the youngest-ever Formula One pole-sitter. As a result, Ricciardo beat Verstappen to pole position by just 0.026 seconds.<ref>{{Citation|title=2018 Mexican Grand Prix: Qualifying Highlights|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SVTDYyXP7E0|access-date=19 January 2022|archive-date=19 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220119233750/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SVTDYyXP7E0|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Max Verstappen unhappy after missing out on history-making pole position|url=https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/11533294/max-verstappen-unhappy-after-missing-out-on-history-making-pole-position|access-date=12 February 2022|publisher=Sky Sports|language=en|archive-date=12 February 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220212120158/https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/11533294/max-verstappen-unhappy-after-missing-out-on-history-making-pole-position|url-status=live}}</ref> Verstappen had a better start than Ricciardo and took the lead of the race into the first corner, overtaking the fast-starting Mercedes of Lewis Hamilton. Verstappen earned his fifth career win in Mexico.<ref>{{Citation|title=2018 Mexican Grand Prix: Race Highlights|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=d1-VK12FZhs|access-date=19 January 2022|archive-date=19 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220119233748/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=d1-VK12FZhs|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Mexican Grand Prix 2018 report – Verstappen wins in Mexico as Hamilton takes fifth title|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.f1-2018-mexican-grand-prix-report.43bcuMZV3i8yk2a8kQw06w.html|access-date=17 February 2022|publisher=Formula One|language=en|archive-date=29 October 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181029014936/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.f1-2018-mexican-grand-prix-report.43bcuMZV3i8yk2a8kQw06w.html|url-status=live}}</ref> He was poised to win the [[2018 Brazilian Grand Prix]], having overtaken Räikkönen, Vettel, Bottas, and Hamilton. However, he collided with [[Force India]] driver [[Esteban Ocon]] who was trying to unlap himself on faster tyres.<ref>{{Citation|title=Verstappen And Ocon Collide {{!}} 2018 Brazilian Grand Prix|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6LSAaVq4Dsw|access-date=19 January 2022|archive-date=19 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220119233744/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6LSAaVq4Dsw|url-status=live}}</ref> Ocon received a 10-second stop-and-go penalty for the incident. After the collision with Ocon, Verstappen finished in second place behind Hamilton. During an argument with Ocon after the race, Verstappen pushed the Force India driver, for which he was given two days of "public service" as a penalty by the FIA.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/139986/verstappen-given-public-service-for-ocon-shove|title=FIA gives Max Verstappen 'public service' for Esteban Ocon shove|last=Freeman|first=Glenn|work=Autosport|access-date=12 November 2018|archive-date=11 November 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181111214724/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/139986/verstappen-given-public-service-for-ocon-shove|url-status=live}}</ref> He then finished his season with another podium as he finished third in Abu Dhabi.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/results.html/2018/races/999/abu-dhabi/race-result.html |title=Formula 1 2018 Etihad Airways Abu Dhabi Grand Prix – Race Result |publisher=Formula One |date=25 November 2018 |access-date=25 November 2018 |archive-date=13 January 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210113155249/https://www.formula1.com/en/results.html/2018/races/999/abu-dhabi/race-result.html |url-status=live }}</ref>

Verstappen ended the season in fourth place in the championship with 249 points, claiming two wins, eleven podium finishes, and two fastest laps.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Max Verstappen in 2018|url=https://www.racing-statistics.com/en/drivers/compare/max-verstappen/seasons/2018|access-date=19 December 2021|website=Formula 1 Statistics|archive-date=19 December 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211219093227/https://www.racing-statistics.com/en/drivers/compare/max-verstappen/seasons/2018|url-status=live}}</ref>

====2019 season====
[[File:Max Verstappen during Hungarian Formula 1 GP.jpg|thumb|Verstappen at the [[2019 Hungarian Grand Prix]], where he started on pole position for the first time in his career.]]
In [[2019 Formula One World Championship|2019]] Red Bull switched from Renault to [[Honda in Formula One|Honda]] power units.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Red Bull agree deal to run Honda engine technology until 2025|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.breaking-red-bull-agree-deal-to-run-honda-engine-technology-until-2025.3wmTSMrtsv6miuwqApz8IT.html|access-date=19 January 2022|publisher=Formula One|archive-date=15 February 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210215215037/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.breaking-red-bull-agree-deal-to-run-honda-engine-technology-until-2025.3wmTSMrtsv6miuwqApz8IT.html|url-status=live}}</ref> After Ricciardo moved to the [[Renault in Formula One|Renault]] team for 2019, Verstappen was joined at Red Bull by [[Pierre Gasly]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Pierre Gasly joins Red Bull for 2019|url=https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/11477951/pierre-gasly-joins-red-bull-for-f1-2019|access-date=19 January 2022|publisher=Sky Sports|archive-date=5 March 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220305224221/https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/11477951/pierre-gasly-joins-red-bull-for-f1-2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Verstappen qualified in fourth and finished third in [[2019 Australian Grand Prix|Australia]], the first podium finish for a [[Honda in Formula One|Honda]]-powered driver since the [[2008 British Grand Prix]].<ref>{{Cite web|date=17 March 2019|title=F1 Australian Grand Prix 2019: Max Verstappen sends ominous Red Bull message after Honda milestone|url=https://www.foxsports.com.au/motorsport/formula-one/f1-australian-grand-prix-2019-max-verstappen-race-results-red-bull-honda-renault-video-latest-news/news-story/9d6d29140487e11eacfa8296e1f95f22|access-date=11 October 2021|work=Fox Sports|archive-date=28 October 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211028172923/https://www.foxsports.com.au/motorsport/formula-one/f1-australian-grand-prix-2019-max-verstappen-race-results-red-bull-honda-renault-video-latest-news/news-story/9d6d29140487e11eacfa8296e1f95f22|url-status=live}}</ref> Verstappen was on course for a second third-place finish in [[2019 Bahrain Grand Prix|Bahrain]] before a late safety car prevented him from overtaking Charles Leclerc's ailing Ferrari, keeping him in fourth place.<ref>{{Citation|title=2019 Bahrain Grand Prix: Race Highlights|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0VjWY--QdMA|access-date=19 January 2022|archive-date=24 April 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220424225323/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0VjWY--QdMA|url-status=live}}</ref> Two more fourth-place finishes followed in [[2019 Chinese Grand Prix|China]] and [[2019 Azerbaijan Grand Prix|Azerbaijan]], and a podium in [[2019 Spanish Grand Prix|Spain]] in third place.<ref>{{Cite web|title=F1 Results – 2019 Spanish Grand Prix|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/formula1/2019/spanish-grand-prix/results|access-date=19 January 2022|publisher=BBC Sport|archive-date=24 April 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220424225314/https://www.bbc.com/sport/formula1/2019/spanish-grand-prix/results|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=F1 Results – 2019 Azerbaijan Grand Prix|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/formula1/2019/azerbaijan-grand-prix/results/race|access-date=19 January 2022|publisher=BBC Sport|archive-date=24 April 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220424225311/https://www.bbc.com/sport/formula1/2019/azerbaijan-grand-prix/results/race|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=F1 Results – 2019 Chinese Grand Prix|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/formula1/2019/chinese-grand-prix/results|access-date=19 January 2022|publisher=BBC Sport|archive-date=13 October 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221013203417/https://www.bbc.com/sport/formula1/2019/chinese-grand-prix/results|url-status=live}}</ref> In [[2019 Monaco Grand Prix|Monaco]], Verstappen qualified in third place. He was released into the path of Valtteri Bottas during the drivers' pit stops, gaining second place but receiving a 5-second penalty as a result. Verstappen crossed the line in second place but was demoted to fourth by the penalty.<ref>{{Cite web|date=26 May 2019|title=Verstappen given penalty points for failing to avoid contact · RaceFans|url=https://www.racefans.net/2019/05/26/verstappen-given-penalty-points-for-failing-to-avoid-contact/|access-date=11 October 2021|website=RaceFans|archive-date=23 October 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211023170821/https://www.racefans.net/2019/05/26/verstappen-given-penalty-points-for-failing-to-avoid-contact/|url-status=live}}</ref>

In [[2019 Canadian Grand Prix|Canada]], Verstappen's final lap in the second qualifying session was hampered by a red flag brought out by [[Kevin Magnussen]]'s crash. This caused Verstappen to qualify 11th and start the race in ninth place.<ref>{{Cite web|date=8 June 2019|title=F1 Canadian Grand Prix 2019 qualifying results: Daniel Ricciardo stuns with best result since October as Sebastian Vettel snatches pole|url=https://www.foxsports.com.au/motorsport/formula-one/f1-canadian-grand-prix-2019-live-qualifying-results-timings-daniel-ricciardo-renault-lewis-hamilton-timesheets-updates-blog/news-story/95ac6b8933fff5af9a310a512de60366|url-status=live|access-date=11 January 2022|work=Fox Sports|archive-date=11 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220111041408/https://www.foxsports.com.au/motorsport/formula-one/f1-canadian-grand-prix-2019-live-qualifying-results-timings-daniel-ricciardo-renault-lewis-hamilton-timesheets-updates-blog/news-story/95ac6b8933fff5af9a310a512de60366}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Fair|first=Asher|date=9 June 2019|title=Formula 1: Provisional starting grid for 2019 Canadian Grand Prix|url=https://beyondtheflag.com/2019/06/09/formula-1-provisional-starting-grid-2019-canadian-grand-prix/|url-status=live|access-date=11 January 2022|website=Beyond the Flag|archive-date=11 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220111041417/https://beyondtheflag.com/2019/06/09/formula-1-provisional-starting-grid-2019-canadian-grand-prix/}}</ref> He later recovered to finish fifth.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Richards|first=Giles|date=9 June 2019|title=Lewis Hamilton handed Canadian Grand Prix win after Vettel's penalty pain|url=http://www.theguardian.com/sport/2019/jun/09/lewis-hamilton-canadian-grand-prix-vettel-penalty|url-status=live|access-date=11 January 2022|website=The Guardian|archive-date=5 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220105160525/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2019/jun/09/lewis-hamilton-canadian-grand-prix-vettel-penalty}}</ref> In [[2019 French Grand Prix|France]] he started and finished in fourth place.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Standings|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/results.html|url-status=live|access-date=19 January 2022|publisher=Formula One|archive-date=28 October 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141028202800/http://www.formula1.com/results/driver/2001/40.html}}</ref> In [[2019 Austrian Grand Prix|Austria]], Verstappen started third but suffered a poor start, dropping down to eighth. After a charge towards the front, he made his way up to second before controversially passing Leclerc for the lead of the race with three laps to go.<ref>{{Citation|title=Verstappen's Stunning Fightback {{!}} 2019 Austrian Grand Prix|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cV0G1zN8kJU|access-date=19 January 2022|archive-date=13 October 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221013203250/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cV0G1zN8kJU|url-status=live}}</ref> This marked the first Honda-powered race victory since the [[2006 Hungarian Grand Prix]].<ref>{{Cite news|last1=McVeigh (earlier)|first1=Niall|last2=Unwin (now)|first2=Will|date=30 June 2019|title=F1: Verstappen's win stands after Austrian Grand Prix stewards inquiry – as it happened|work=The Guardian|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/live/2019/jun/30/f1-formula-one-austrian-grand-prix-live|access-date=11 January 2022|issn=0261-3077|archive-date=11 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220111041738/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/live/2019/jun/30/f1-formula-one-austrian-grand-prix-live|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=1 July 2019|title=Honda hails new beginning after first F1 win since 2006|url=https://www.autoblog.com/2019/07/01/honda-hail-new-beginning-after-first-f1-win-since-2006/|url-status=live|access-date=11 January 2022|website=Autoblog|archive-date=13 October 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221013203242/https://www.autoblog.com/2019/07/01/honda-hail-new-beginning-after-first-f1-win-since-2006/}}</ref> In [[2019 British Grand Prix|Britain]], Verstappen, running in third place,<ref>{{Cite web|last=Simpson|first=Christopher|date=12 July 2019|title=F1 British Grand Prix 2019 Qualifying: Results, Times from Friday's Practice|url=https://bleacherreport.com/articles/2845285-british-f1-grand-prix-2019-qualifying-results-times-from-fridays-practice|url-status=live|access-date=11 January 2022|website=Bleacher Report|archive-date=13 October 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221013203242/https://bleacherreport.com/articles/2845285-british-f1-grand-prix-2019-qualifying-results-times-from-fridays-practice}}</ref> was hit from behind during an overtake attempt by Sebastian Vettel and spun into the gravel. Verstappen was able to continue and crossed the line in fifth place.<ref>{{Cite web|date=14 July 2019|title=British Grand Prix 2019 race report: Hamilton victorious as Verstappen and Vettel collide in Silverstone thriller|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.hamilton-victorious-as-verstappen-and-vettel-collide-in-silverstone.3yHjP4nXKPkt4HYJQ7Bagt.html|url-status=live|access-date=11 January 2022|publisher=Formula One|archive-date=14 July 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190714153942/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.hamilton-victorious-as-verstappen-and-vettel-collide-in-silverstone.3yHjP4nXKPkt4HYJQ7Bagt.html}}</ref>

The wet and chaotic [[2019 German Grand Prix|German Grand Prix]] began similarly to the race in Austria for Verstappen, as a poor start caused him to fall behind. However, he would inherit the lead midway through the race after a crash by race leader Hamilton.<ref>{{Citation|title=2019 German Grand Prix: Race Highlights|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RYHQmBULhLc|access-date=19 January 2022|archive-date=19 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220119235641/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RYHQmBULhLc|url-status=live}}</ref> Verstappen would go on to extend his lead after the track began to dry, claiming his second victory of the season.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Richards|first=Giles|date=28 July 2019|title=Max Verstappen wins thrilling German GP after Lewis Hamilton error|url=http://www.theguardian.com/sport/2019/jul/28/max-verstappen-wins-german-grand-prix-hamilton-error|url-status=live|access-date=29 December 2021|website=The Guardian|archive-date=15 November 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211115040807/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2019/jul/28/max-verstappen-wins-german-grand-prix-hamilton-error}}</ref> In [[2019 Hungarian Grand Prix|Hungary]], he claimed the first pole position of his career and led most of the race before being passed in the closing laps by Hamilton, who had made another stop for fresh tyres in a gamble to catch the leader.<ref>{{Cite web|date=4 August 2019|title=Hungarian Grand Prix 2019 F1 race report: Hamilton brilliantly hunts down Verstappen to snatch Hungary victory|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.hamilton-brilliantly-hunts-down-verstappen-to-snatch-hungary-victory.4QPgPYGdCXqeEirMjUEhZU.html|url-status=live|access-date=29 December 2021|publisher=Formula One|archive-date=29 December 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211229031344/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.hamilton-brilliantly-hunts-down-verstappen-to-snatch-hungary-victory.4QPgPYGdCXqeEirMjUEhZU.html}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Verstappen takes maiden career pole in thrilling Hungary qualifying|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.verstappen-takes-maiden-career-pole-in-thrilling-hungary-qualifying.5AABsomaDmZaBusQxjCZuP.html|access-date=19 January 2022|publisher=Formula One|archive-date=18 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220118131304/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.verstappen-takes-maiden-career-pole-in-thrilling-hungary-qualifying.5AABsomaDmZaBusQxjCZuP.html|url-status=live}}</ref>
[[File:Fórmula 1 – Grande Prêmio do Brasil de F1 2019 (49080565726).jpg|thumb|right|Verstappen on the podium after winning the [[2019 Brazilian Grand Prix]]]]
Before the [[2019 Belgian Grand Prix|Belgian Grand Prix]], Verstappen received a new teammate in Alexander Albon after Pierre Gasly was demoted back to Toro Rosso.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Albon to replace Gasly at Red Bull from Belgium|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.albon-to-replace-gasly-at-red-bull-from-belgium.5f9BkwxuJ5TF86EPKqqwJa.html|access-date=19 January 2022|publisher=Formula One|archive-date=24 December 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201224174052/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.albon-to-replace-gasly-at-red-bull-from-belgium.5f9BkwxuJ5TF86EPKqqwJa.html|url-status=live}}</ref> In the race, Verstappen had a poor start and collided with Kimi Räikkönen at the first corner, resulting in suspension damage and causing Verstappen's first retirement of the season.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Verstappen and Raikkonen bemoan first-lap clash|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.verstappen-and-raikkonen-bemoan-first-lap-clash.4LEpXoR5Ha6QXl9xd2Ovty.html|access-date=19 January 2022|publisher=Formula One|archive-date=3 September 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190903173008/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.verstappen-and-raikkonen-bemoan-first-lap-clash.4LEpXoR5Ha6QXl9xd2Ovty.html|url-status=live}}</ref> In [[2019 Italian Grand Prix|Italy]], he did not set a time during qualifying after his car lost power in Q1, but he was already required to start from the back of the grid due to an engine component penalty.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Media|first=P. A.|date=4 September 2019|title=Penalty shunts Max Verstappen to back of F1 grid for Italian Grand Prix|url=http://www.theguardian.com/sport/2019/sep/04/max-verstappen-engine-penalty-monza-italian-grand-prix-back-grid|access-date=19 January 2022|website=The Guardian|archive-date=24 April 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220424225312/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2019/sep/04/max-verstappen-engine-penalty-monza-italian-grand-prix-back-grid|url-status=live}}</ref> After damaging his front wing on the first lap, he recovered to finish the race in eighth place.<ref>{{Citation|title=2019 Italian Grand Prix: Race Highlights|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=h-ce3gPMsGc|access-date=19 January 2022|archive-date=3 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303104046/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=h-ce3gPMsGc&app=desktop|url-status=live}}</ref> third and fourth-place finishes followed in [[2019 Singapore Grand Prix|Singapore]] and [[2019 Russian Grand Prix|Russia]] respectively.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Singapore Grand Prix 2019 – F1 Race|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/racing/2019/Singapore.html|access-date=19 January 2022|publisher=Formula One|archive-date=11 November 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111192803/https://www.formula1.com/en/racing/2019/Singapore.html|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=F1 Results – 2019 Russian Grand Prix|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/formula1/2019/russian-grand-prix/results|access-date=19 January 2022|publisher=BBC Sport|archive-date=24 April 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220424225311/https://www.bbc.com/sport/formula1/2019/russian-grand-prix/results|url-status=live}}</ref> After suffering damage in a first-lap collision with Charles Leclerc in [[2019 Japanese Grand Prix|Japan]], Verstappen suffered his second retirement of the season.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Japanese Grand Prix 2019: Verstappen blasts 'irresponsible' Leclerc after Lap 1 contact|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.verstappen-blasts-irresponsible-leclerc-after-lap-1-contact.4yO6ylOGvL0uzhJZ98myCz.html|access-date=19 January 2022|publisher=Formula One|archive-date=24 April 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220424225325/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.verstappen-blasts-irresponsible-leclerc-after-lap-1-contact.4yO6ylOGvL0uzhJZ98myCz.html|url-status=live}}</ref>

In [[2019 Mexican Grand Prix|Mexico]], he qualified in first place after setting the fastest lap-time of the session, before being handed a grid penalty for ignoring [[Racing flags#Yellow flag|yellow flags]] after a crash by Valtteri Bottas.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Mexican Grand Prix 2019 qualifying report: Verstappen takes sensational Mexican pole as Bottas crashes|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.verstappen-takes-sensational-mexican-pole-as-bottas-suffers-big-crash.2iQWb1vLhcfSRBothUZyzd.html|access-date=19 January 2022|publisher=Formula One|archive-date=28 October 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191028220105/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.verstappen-takes-sensational-mexican-pole-as-bottas-suffers-big-crash.2iQWb1vLhcfSRBothUZyzd.html|url-status=live}}</ref> Verstappen suffered a puncture early in the race after making contact with Bottas, falling to the back of the field before eventually recovering to sixth place.<ref>{{Cite web|date=27 October 2019|title=Mexican Grand Prix 2019 report & highlights: Hamilton closes in on title with supreme Mexico victory|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.mexican-grand-prix-2019-report-and-highlights.2GCUEuCYRquG0pcZeGZuYz.html|url-status=live|access-date=29 December 2021|publisher=Formula One|archive-date=28 October 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191028191133/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.mexican-grand-prix-2019-report-and-highlights.2GCUEuCYRquG0pcZeGZuYz.html}}</ref> A third-place finish in the [[2019 United States Grand Prix|United States]] followed, before Verstappen took the second pole position of his career with a 1:07.508 pole lap time in [[2019 Brazilian Grand Prix|Brazil]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=United States Grand Prix 2019 – F1 Race|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/racing/2019/United_States.html|access-date=19 January 2022|publisher=Formula One|archive-date=13 September 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200913021847/https://www.formula1.com/en/racing/2019/United_States.html|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Brazilian Grand Prix 2019 qualifying report: Brazilian Grand Prix report: Verstappen snatches sensational Interlagos pole|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.verstappen-snatches-sensational-interlagos-pole.6QOPSwc0ZAKtVuAsXoaoDI.html|access-date=19 January 2022|publisher=Formula One|archive-date=12 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220112034257/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.verstappen-snatches-sensational-interlagos-pole.6QOPSwc0ZAKtVuAsXoaoDI.html|url-status=live}}</ref> In a chaotic race, he passed Lewis Hamilton for the lead on two occasions before going on to claim his third victory of the season.<ref>{{Citation|title=2019 Brazilian Grand Prix: Race Highlights|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3WZeoOkMf0Y|access-date=19 January 2022|archive-date=24 April 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220424225323/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3WZeoOkMf0Y|url-status=live}}</ref> Verstappen ended the season with a second-place finish in [[2019 Abu Dhabi Grand Prix|Abu Dhabi]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Abu Dhabi Grand Prix 2019 race report and highlights: Hamilton rounds off title-winning season with dominant Abu Dhabi win|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.abu-dhabi-grand-prix-2019-race-report-highlights.3W60C6jaqAMKYqcblkhGqg.html|access-date=19 January 2022|publisher=Formula One|archive-date=2 December 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191202061826/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.abu-dhabi-grand-prix-2019-race-report-highlights.3W60C6jaqAMKYqcblkhGqg.html|url-status=live}}</ref>

Verstappen finished the 2019 season in third place in the championship with 278 points. He claimed three race victories, nine podium finishes, two pole positions, and three fastest laps.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Max Verstappen in 2019|url=https://www.racing-statistics.com/en/drivers/compare/max-verstappen/seasons/2019|access-date=19 December 2021|website=Formula 1 Statistics|archive-date=19 December 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211219094726/https://www.racing-statistics.com/en/drivers/compare/max-verstappen/seasons/2019|url-status=live}}</ref>

====2020 season====

In 2020, Verstappen signed a contract extension to race for Red Bull until the end of {{f1|2023}}.<ref name="2023 contract">{{cite web |date=7 January 2020 |title=Max Verstappen extends contract with Aston Martin Red Bull Racing |url=https://verstappen.nl/en/article/3936/ |access-date=7 January 2020 |website=verstappen.nl |archive-date=29 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229041605/https://www.verstappen.nl/en/article/3936/ |url-status=live }}</ref>
[[File:Max Verstappen, 2020 pre-season testing.jpg|thumb|Verstappen at [[2020 Formula One pre-season testing|pre-season testing in 2020]]]]
Verstappen continued to race for Red Bull in {{F1|2020}}, alongside Albon. At the [[2020 Austrian Grand Prix]], he started second, but retired early in the race after a flywheel-related problem caused an electronic issue within the power unit.<ref>{{Cite web|date=10 July 2020|title=Albon's DNF likely caused by Hamilton clash, not Honda fault|url=https://the-race.com/formula-1/albons-dnf-likely-caused-by-hamilton-clash-not-honda-fault/|access-date=21 July 2020|website=The Race|archive-date=21 July 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200721123813/https://the-race.com/formula-1/albons-dnf-likely-caused-by-hamilton-clash-not-honda-fault/|url-status=live}}</ref> Honda introduced countermeasures in response to the retirement.<ref>{{Cite web|date=9 July 2020|title=Red Bull, Honda have countermeasures for engine issues|url=https://the-race.com/formula-1/honda-has-countermeasures-for-red-bulls-engine-issues/|access-date=21 July 2020|website=The Race|archive-date=21 July 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200721123808/https://the-race.com/formula-1/honda-has-countermeasures-for-red-bulls-engine-issues/|url-status=live}}</ref>

At the [[2020 Hungarian Grand Prix]], he crashed in wet conditions during the [[formation lap]] while he was on his way to the starting grid,<ref>{{Citation|title=Max Verstappen Crashes On Way To Grid {{!}} 2020 Hungarian Grand Prix|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=k-HpHDpeF8E|access-date=20 January 2022|archive-date=20 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220120003458/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=k-HpHDpeF8E|url-status=live}}</ref> but he was able to drive the car back to the grid where his mechanics fixed the suspension of the car in the short time that was left before the start of the race.<ref>{{Citation|title=INSIDE STORY: How Red Bull Performed a Mechanical Miracle in Hungary|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IGwm1QmwN9s|access-date=20 January 2022|archive-date=20 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220120003454/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IGwm1QmwN9s|url-status=live}}</ref> After the repairs, Verstappen progressed from seventh place on the grid to second place by the end of the race.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.second-feels-like-a-win-says-verstappen-as-he-recovers-from-pre-race-crash.5rbSAYCw1F215d1dlFvW8A.html|title='Second feels like a win' says Verstappen as he recovers from pre-race crash to podium|publisher=Formula One|access-date=21 July 2020|archive-date=20 July 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200720204302/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.second-feels-like-a-win-says-verstappen-as-he-recovers-from-pre-race-crash.5rbSAYCw1F215d1dlFvW8A.html|url-status=live}}</ref> Verstappen won the [[70th Anniversary Grand Prix]] at [[Silverstone Circuit|Silverstone]], having started from fourth.<ref name="MVvolgensGR">{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2020/aug/09/f1-max-verstappen-70th-anniversary-grand-prix-lewis-hamilton|title=Max Verstappen roars to spectacular victory in 70th Anniversary Grand Prix|author=Giles Richards|date=9 August 2020|publisher=[[The Guardian]], London|access-date=9 August 2020|archive-date=9 August 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200809153202/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2020/aug/09/f1-max-verstappen-70th-anniversary-grand-prix-lewis-hamilton|url-status=live}}</ref>

Verstappen clinched second place at the [[2020 Spanish Grand Prix|Spanish Grand Prix]], after qualifying in third.<ref>{{Cite web|title=2020 F1 Spanish Grand Prix qualifying results & grid lineup|url=https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/spanish-gp-grid-qualifying-results/4857117/amp/|access-date=20 January 2022|website=Motorsport.com|date=15 August 2020 |archive-date=20 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220120003452/https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/spanish-gp-grid-qualifying-results/4857117/amp/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Spanish Grand Prix 2020 – F1 Race|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/racing/2020/Spain.html|url-status=live|access-date=20 January 2022|publisher=Formula One|archive-date=11 January 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210111012227/https://www.formula1.com/en/racing/2020/Spain.html}}</ref> At the [[2020 Belgian Grand Prix]], he scored a podium in third place, following his third place on the starting grid.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Belgian Grand Prix 2020 – F1 Race|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/racing/2020/Belgium.html|url-status=live|access-date=20 January 2022|publisher=Formula One|archive-date=19 January 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210119083704/https://www.formula1.com/en/racing/2020/Belgium.html}}</ref> He suffered from two consecutive DNFs at the [[2020 Italian Grand Prix|Italian]] and [[2020 Tuscan Grand Prix|Tuscan]] Grands Prix after which he lost second place in the Championship.<ref>{{Citation|title=2020 Italian Grand Prix: Race Highlights|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TB5yhZdF8SI|access-date=20 January 2022|archive-date=20 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220120003452/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TB5yhZdF8SI|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|title=2020 Tuscan Grand Prix: Race Highlights|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=R-Yq1AlIwsc|access-date=20 January 2022|archive-date=20 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220120003456/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=R-Yq1AlIwsc|url-status=live}}</ref> At the [[2020 Russian Grand Prix|Russian Grand Prix]], Verstappen finished the race in second, his seventh podium finish of 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Russian Grand Prix 2020 – F1 Race|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/racing/2020/Russia.html|url-status=live|access-date=20 January 2022|publisher=Formula One|archive-date=19 January 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210119083834/https://www.formula1.com/en/racing/2020/Russia.html}}</ref> At the [[2020 Eifel Grand Prix|Eifel Grand Prix]], Verstappen finished in second after qualifying in third.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Eifel Grand Prix 2020 – German F1 Race|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/racing/2020/Germany.html|access-date=20 January 2022|publisher=Formula One|archive-date=19 January 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210119083909/https://www.formula1.com/en/racing/2020/Germany.html|url-status=live}}</ref> He also managed to get the fastest lap of the race.<ref>{{Citation|title=Verstappen's Nurburgring Lap Record: Fastest Lap {{!}} 2020 Eifel Grand Prix {{!}} DHL|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1TRkAjsB7MA|access-date=20 January 2022|archive-date=20 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220120003500/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1TRkAjsB7MA|url-status=live}}</ref> At the [[2020 Portuguese Grand Prix|Portuguese Grand Prix]], Verstappen qualified third, however a poor first lap meant that he dropped back down the order to fifth place. He recovered to third and took his 40th podium in Formula 1.<ref>{{Citation|title=2020 Portuguese Grand Prix: Race Highlights|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nQ8du5ysxTI|access-date=20 January 2022|archive-date=25 December 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211225143139/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nQ8du5ysxTI|url-status=live}}</ref> At the [[2020 Emilia Romagna Grand Prix|Emilia Romagna Grand Prix]], Verstappen looked set to claim second due to [[Valtteri Bottas]]' ailing Mercedes slowing down, but a sudden puncture denied him any chance of a podium finish; Verstappen spun, resulting in his fourth retirement of the 2020 season.<ref>{{Citation|title=Verstappen Crashes Out of Podium Position After Right Rear Failure|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gYcA_ivpSxE|access-date=19 January 2022|archive-date=13 October 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221013203414/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gYcA_ivpSxE|url-status=live}}</ref>

During Free Practice for the Portuguese Grand Prix, Verstappen was criticised for comments he made on the team radio after a collision with [[Lance Stroll]], where he used the words "retard" and "mongol" in response to the clash. Verstappen admitted following the session that the word choices he used were "not correct." The Mongolian government and the Mongol identity asked Verstappen to apologise for the comments; the Mongolian government also urged the [[Fédération Internationale de l'Automobile|FIA]] to take action on the comments he made.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Cooper |first1=Adam |title=Portimao radio comments 'not correct', says Verstappen |publisher=Motorsport.com |url=https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/verstappen-radio-outburst-portugal-stroll/4901418/ |date=30 October 2020 |access-date=12 November 2020 |archive-date=1 November 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201101033201/https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/verstappen-radio-outburst-portugal-stroll/4901418/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Boxall-Legge |first1=Jake |title=Mongolian government wants FIA to act on Verstappen comments |publisher=Motorsport.com |url=https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/mongolia-foreign-minister-letter-verstappen-comments/4901947/ |date=31 October 2020 |access-date=12 November 2020 |archive-date=10 November 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201110110951/https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/mongolia-foreign-minister-letter-verstappen-comments/4901947/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

Verstappen finished the 2020 season in third place in the championship with 214 points. He claimed two race victories, eleven podium finishes, one pole position, and three fastest laps.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Max Verstappen in 2020|url=https://www.racing-statistics.com/en/drivers/compare/max-verstappen/seasons/2020|access-date=19 December 2021|website=Formula 1 Statistics|archive-date=19 December 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211219094724/https://www.racing-statistics.com/en/drivers/compare/max-verstappen/seasons/2020|url-status=live}}</ref>

====2021 season: World Champion====
[[File:FIA F1 Austria 2021 Nr. 33 Verstappen.jpg|thumb|Verstappen at the 2021 Austrian Grand Prix]]
At the [[2021 Bahrain Grand Prix|Bahrain Grand Prix]], Verstappen topped all the practice sessions and subsequently took a career fourth pole position. This was the first time he achieved back-to-back pole positions.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Max Verstappen takes pole position in F1 Bahrain Grand Prix, Daniel Ricciardo sixth|date=27 March 2021|url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2021-03-28/max-verstappen-takes-pole-position-in-f1-bahrain-grand-prix/100033884|publisher=Australian Broadcasting Corporation|access-date=30 March 2021|archive-date=30 March 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210330114816/https://www.abc.net.au/news/2021-03-28/max-verstappen-takes-pole-position-in-f1-bahrain-grand-prix/100033884|url-status=live}}</ref> He fought Lewis Hamilton for the race victory, and on lap 53 Verstappen overtook Hamilton, but went off track whilst doing so, resulting in him being instructed by race control to let Hamilton back into the lead and ultimately finishing second behind Hamilton.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.it-is-what-it-is-verstappen-philosophical-about-surrendering-lead-to.1etBIWyqgV0mdhLUCGjqyJ.html|title='It is what it is' – Verstappen philosophical about surrendering lead to Hamilton following off-track pass|publisher=Formula One|access-date=30 March 2021|archive-date=30 March 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210330120727/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.it-is-what-it-is-verstappen-philosophical-about-surrendering-lead-to.1etBIWyqgV0mdhLUCGjqyJ.html|url-status=live}}</ref> At the next race, the [[2021 Emilia Romagna Grand Prix|Emilia Romagna Grand Prix]], Verstappen qualified third with teammate [[Sergio Pérez]] second, marking the first time he was out-qualified by a teammate since the [[2019 Italian Grand Prix]].<ref>{{Cite web|title='We're not robots' – Verstappen on 'messy' Q3 that led to being out-qualified by a team mate for first time since 2018|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.were-not-robots-verstappen-on-messy-q3-that-led-to-being-out-qualified-by-a.a7GbWPG2MnJEtyXOmP1x6.html|access-date=19 January 2022|publisher=Formula One|archive-date=20 October 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211020100943/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.were-not-robots-verstappen-on-messy-q3-that-led-to-being-out-qualified-by-a.a7GbWPG2MnJEtyXOmP1x6.html|url-status=live}}</ref> At the race start, Verstappen was able to pass both Pérez and pole-sitter Lewis Hamilton to take the lead. He remained in the lead after the first round of pit stops as well as the restart, following the race being suspended on lap 33. Rival Hamilton finished second, reducing his championship lead over Verstappen to one point.<ref>{{Citation|title=Race Highlights {{!}} 2021 Emilia Romagna Grand Prix|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ds0BC8RDJ5o|access-date=19 January 2022|archive-date=13 October 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221013203252/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ds0BC8RDJ5o|url-status=live}}</ref> In the following [[2021 Portuguese Grand Prix|Portuguese Grand Prix]], Verstappen finished second after a long battle with Lewis Hamilton.<ref>{{Citation|title=Race Highlights {{!}} 2021 Portuguese Grand Prix|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-9-8gvYantk|access-date=19 January 2022|archive-date=24 April 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220424225321/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-9-8gvYantk|url-status=live}}</ref> At the [[2021 Spanish Grand Prix|Spanish Grand Prix]], the battle between Verstappen and Hamilton continued, with Hamilton employing a faster two-stop strategy versus Verstappen's one-stop race. This provided Hamilton the advantage of faster tyres, allowing him to overtake Verstappen with several laps remaining in the race. Hamilton took the victory, with Verstappen taking second and the fastest lap, increasing Hamilton's championship lead to 14 points.<ref>{{Cite web|title=2021 Spanish Grand Prix race report and highlights: Late pass secures Hamilton victory in Spain after race-long battle with Verstappen|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.late-pass-secures-hamilton-victory-in-spain-after-race-long-battle-with.5xOxaR8dsRf8zn11GGd8dN.html|access-date=18 May 2021|publisher=Formula One|archive-date=9 May 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210509175353/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.late-pass-secures-hamilton-victory-in-spain-after-race-long-battle-with.5xOxaR8dsRf8zn11GGd8dN.html|url-status=live}}</ref>

At the next race in [[2021 Monaco Grand Prix|Monaco]], Verstappen qualified second behind [[Charles Leclerc]],<ref>{{Cite web|title=2021 Monaco GP Qualifying: Verstappen rages at Leclerc crash red flags|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/video.2021-monaco-gp-qualifying-verstappen-rages-at-leclerc-crash-red-flags.1700470908172196475.html|access-date=19 January 2022|publisher=Formula One|archive-date=10 March 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220310032538/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/video.2021-monaco-gp-qualifying-verstappen-rages-at-leclerc-crash-red-flags.1700470908172196475.html|url-status=live}}</ref> but Leclerc suffered a driveshaft failure on the way to the grid and was unable to start the race. Verstappen controlled the race from the front on the way to victory. Hamilton (who qualified seventh) finished seventh, though claiming an extra championship point by setting the fastest race lap. The result enabled Verstappen to take the lead in the Drivers' Championship for the first time in his career, by a margin of four points over Hamilton.<ref>{{cite web |last=Benson |first=Andrew |title=Monaco Grand Prix: Max Verstappen takes title lead from Lewis Hamilton with win |publisher=BBC Sport |date=23 May 2021 |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/formula1/57220586 |access-date=23 May 2021 |archive-date=23 May 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210523152235/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/formula1/57220586 |url-status=live }}</ref> At the [[2021 Azerbaijan Grand Prix|Azerbaijan Grand Prix]], Verstappen qualified third behind Leclerc and Hamilton.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Verstappen curses 'stupid' qualifying session in Baku as he loses another chance of pole to red flag|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.verstappen-curses-stupid-qualifying-in-baku-as-he-loses-another-chance-of.71o8PO388LO4nTLXqmE0SC.html|access-date=19 January 2022|publisher=Formula One|archive-date=25 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220125074130/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.verstappen-curses-stupid-qualifying-in-baku-as-he-loses-another-chance-of.71o8PO388LO4nTLXqmE0SC.html|url-status=live}}</ref> Verstappen and Hamilton passed Leclerc in the opening laps before Verstappen took the lead by way of a faster pitstop. Verstappen would comfortably hold the lead until lap 46 when he suffered a tyre failure causing him to crash at high-speed and retire.<ref>{{Citation|title=Verstappen Crashes Out of Lead After Left Rear Failure {{!}} 2021 Azerbaijan Grand Prix|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mgAinVHFwls|access-date=19 January 2022|archive-date=28 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220128103451/https://www.youtube.com/watch?t=32&v=mgAinVHFwls&feature=youtu.be|url-status=live}}</ref> A mistake by Hamilton on the restart dropped him to last place, meaning Verstappen maintained his championship lead.<ref>{{Cite web|title=2021 Azerbaijan Grand Prix race report and highlights: Perez beats Vettel to Baku victory after Verstappen crashes out from lead late on|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.perez-beats-vettel-to-baku-victory-after-verstappen-crashes-out-from-lead.aLIxuNGxwBFgZ4Z8OhuRw.html|access-date=29 June 2021|publisher=Formula One|archive-date=10 June 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210610172247/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.perez-beats-vettel-to-baku-victory-after-verstappen-crashes-out-from-lead.aLIxuNGxwBFgZ4Z8OhuRw.html|url-status=live}}</ref> Verstappen took pole for the [[2021 French Grand Prix|French Grand Prix]].<ref>{{Citation|title=Max Verstappen's Onboard Pole Lap {{!}} 2021 French Grand Prix|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gq5-tSxKIcE|access-date=19 January 2022|archive-date=10 March 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220310191135/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gq5-tSxKIcE|url-status=live}}</ref> Verstappen's mistake on the first lap allowed Hamilton to take the lead which Verstappen retook during the pit stop phase. Verstappen pitted for a second time from the lead and set after the Mercedes duo, overtaking Hamilton for the lead on lap 52 of 53.<ref>{{Citation|title=How Max Verstappen Fought Back To Beat Lewis Hamilton I 2021 French Grand Prix|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=H_Ty1fYKGkQ|access-date=20 January 2022|archive-date=20 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220120011131/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=H_Ty1fYKGkQ|url-status=live}}</ref> He also took the fastest lap point, extending his championship lead to twelve points<ref>{{Cite web|title=2021 French Grand Prix race report & highlights: Verstappen triumphs over Hamilton after late pass in scintillating French Grand Prix|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.verstappen-triumphs-over-hamilton-after-late-pass-in-scintillating-french.22o4zqXsOtjAcFiaBxva2q.html|access-date=29 June 2021|publisher=Formula One|archive-date=21 June 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210621004259/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.verstappen-triumphs-over-hamilton-after-late-pass-in-scintillating-french.22o4zqXsOtjAcFiaBxva2q.html|url-status=live}}</ref> and achieving the first [[List of Formula One driver records#Pole, win, and fastest lap in same race|hat-trick]] of his career.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.french-gp-facts-and-stats-verstappens-first-f1-hat-trick-and-a-special.5RdIdqVagUjxZf5rQ3VASt.html|title=French GP Facts & Stats: Verstappen's first F1 hat-trick, and a special podium for Perez|first=Sean|last=Kelly|date=20 June 2021|publisher=Formula One|access-date=7 July 2022|archive-date=21 June 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210621003951/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.french-gp-facts-and-stats-verstappens-first-f1-hat-trick-and-a-special.5RdIdqVagUjxZf5rQ3VASt.html|url-status=live}}</ref> Verstappen clinched pole position again at the [[2021 Styrian Grand Prix|Styrian Grand Prix]] and led the race from start to finish, to give him his fourth win of the season and further extend his lead to 18 points.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.sportstiger.com/max-verstappen-wins-styrian-gp-2021-beats-lewis-hamilton-and-valtteri-bottas-in-austria/ |title=Max Verstappen wins Styrian GP 2021; beats Lewis Hamilton and Valtteri Bottas in Austria |work=SportsTiger |date=27 June 2021 |access-date=27 June 2021 |archive-date=27 June 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210627144914/https://www.sportstiger.com/max-verstappen-wins-styrian-gp-2021-beats-lewis-hamilton-and-valtteri-bottas-in-austria/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

Verstappen took pole position at the [[2021 Austrian Grand Prix|Austrian Grand Prix]], led every lap from start to finish, set the fastest lap, and won the race for his first career [[grand slam (Formula One)|grand slam]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.verstappen-waltzes-to-second-win-in-a-row-at-red-bull-ring-as-bottas-beats.31KpLIZDzipY9FhputWqf7.html|title=Verstappen waltzes to second win in a row at Red Bull Ring, as Bottas beats Norris to P2|date=4 July 2021|access-date=19 June 2022|publisher=Formula One|archive-date=30 November 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211130235934/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.verstappen-waltzes-to-second-win-in-a-row-at-red-bull-ring-as-bottas-beats.31KpLIZDzipY9FhputWqf7.html|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=4 July 2021|title=F1 – Verstappen extends title lead with Austrian Grand Prix grand slam as Hamilton finishes fourth|url=https://www.fia.com/news/f1-verstappen-extends-title-lead-austrian-grand-prix-grand-slam-hamilton-finishes-fourth|access-date=4 July 2021|website=Federation Internationale de l'Automobile|archive-date=4 July 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210704160816/https://www.fia.com/news/f1-verstappen-extends-title-lead-austrian-grand-prix-grand-slam-hamilton-finishes-fourth|url-status=live}}</ref> being the youngest to do so.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Aggarwal|first=Abhay|date=15 July 2021|title=What Is a Grand Slam in F1?|url=https://www.essentiallysports.com/f1-news-what-is-a-grand-slam-in-f1/|url-status=live|access-date=17 July 2021|website=EssentiallySports|archive-date=17 July 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210717162011/https://www.essentiallysports.com/f1-news-what-is-a-grand-slam-in-f1/}}</ref> With the win, Verstappen also became the first driver to win three races in three consecutive weekends, starting at the French Grand Prix on 20 June, then the Styrian Grand Prix on 27 June and ending with the Austrian Grand Prix on 4 July.<ref>{{Cite web|year=2021|title=Verstappen has little interest in the grand slam: 'As long as we win'|url=https://www.gpblog.com/en/amp/88345/verstappen-has-little-interest-in-the-grand-slam-as-long-as-we-win|url-status=live|access-date=4 July 2021|website=gpblog.com|archive-date=9 July 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210709191340/https://www.gpblog.com/en/amp/88345/verstappen-has-little-interest-in-the-grand-slam-as-long-as-we-win}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=4 July 2021|title=Austrian GP: Post-Race reaction from Max, Perez and Horner|url=https://www.bleachersnews.com/austrian-gp-post-race-reaction-from-max-perez-and-horner/|access-date=4 July 2021|website=Bleachers News|archive-date=9 July 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210709213140/https://www.bleachersnews.com/austrian-gp-post-race-reaction-from-max-perez-and-horner/|url-status=live}}</ref> At the next race; the [[2021 British Grand Prix|British Grand Prix]], Verstappen was involved in a high-speed collision at the ''[[Silverstone Circuit#Circuit|Copse]]'' corner with Hamilton on the first lap. This resulted in a 51 ''[[G-force|g]]'' impact with the barrier.<ref>{{Citation|title=Verstappen & Hamilton Collide at Silverstone {{!}} 2021 British Grand Prix|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oIKel6jVD3Q|access-date=19 January 2022|archive-date=3 July 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220703032242/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oIKel6jVD3Q|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Verstappen's Silverstone crash power unit given the all-clear by Honda after Friday running in Hungary|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.verstappens-silverstone-crash-power-unit-given-the-all-clear-by-honda-after.4gmPYE3cbWVQzNGN1mbYlc.html|access-date=19 January 2022|publisher=Formula One|archive-date=18 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220118142945/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.verstappens-silverstone-crash-power-unit-given-the-all-clear-by-honda-after.4gmPYE3cbWVQzNGN1mbYlc.html|url-status=live}}</ref> He was taken to the Silverstone circuit's medical centre after the crash and was then taken to Coventry hospital for precautionary checks and further assessment, before eventually being discharged at 22:00 local time on Sunday night.<ref>{{Cite web |date=18 July 2021 |title=British GP: Lewis Hamilton wins dramatic home race after big Max Verstappen crash as title lead is cut |url=https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/12358463/british-gp-lewis-hamilton-wins-dramatic-home-race-after-big-max-verstappen-crash-as-title-lead-is-cut |access-date=18 July 2021 |archive-date=17 March 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220317051534/https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/12358463/british-gp-lewis-hamilton-wins-dramatic-home-race-after-big-max-verstappen-crash-as-title-lead-is-cut |url-status=live }}</ref> Hamilton would go on to win the race, reducing Verstappen's lead in the championship to eight points.<ref>{{Cite web|title=2021 British Grand Prix race report & highlights: Hamilton overcomes first-lap collision with Verstappen to hunt down Leclerc for 8th British GP win|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.hamilton-overcomes-first-lap-collision-with-verstappen-to-hunt-down-leclerc.AgFOAxlzlpWSTiHS0Hsbe.html|access-date=19 January 2022|publisher=Formula One|archive-date=18 July 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210718220128/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.hamilton-overcomes-first-lap-collision-with-verstappen-to-hunt-down-leclerc.AgFOAxlzlpWSTiHS0Hsbe.html|url-status=live}}</ref> At the next race, the [[2021 Hungarian Grand Prix|Hungarian Grand Prix]], Verstappen's car suffered damage in a multi-car collision on lap 1, where Mercedes driver Valtteri Bottas was deemed at fault. He ended the race in tenth which was promoted to ninth after Sebastian Vettel was disqualified. The outcome of the race allowed Hamilton to take the lead of the championship.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/31381/12370206/hungarian-gp-max-verstappen-red-bull-rue-brutal-valtteri-bottas-triggered-start-chaos-after-lost-title-leads |title=Hungarian GP: Max Verstappen, Red Bull rue 'brutal' Valtteri Bottas-triggered start chaos after lost title leads |last=Galloway |first=James |date=2 August 2021 |website=skysports.com |access-date=4 August 2021 |archive-date=5 August 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210805035034/https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/31381/12370206/hungarian-gp-max-verstappen-red-bull-rue-brutal-valtteri-bottas-triggered-start-chaos-after-lost-title-leads |url-status=live }}</ref>

Following the summer break, Verstappen qualified on pole at the [[2021 Belgian Grand Prix|Belgian Grand Prix]], ahead of Williams driver [[George Russell (racing driver)|George Russell]] in second and Lewis Hamilton in third.<ref>{{Citation|title=Qualifying Highlights {{!}} 2021 Belgian Grand Prix|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E_CvS-dN99Y|access-date=19 January 2022|archive-date=19 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220119002339/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E_CvS-dN99Y|url-status=live}}</ref> The race was run for three laps, all behind the safety car, with the race official race results taken from the running order at the end of the first lap, with Hamilton and Verstappen both retaining their qualifying positions. As less than 75% of the race distance was completed, half points were awarded, resulting in Verstappen closing the gap to Hamilton to three points.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Benson |first1=Andrew |title=Max Verstappen declared winner of aborted rain-hit Belgian Grand Prix |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/formula1/58377097 |publisher=BBC Sport |access-date=29 August 2021 |archive-date=29 August 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210829172106/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/formula1/58377097 |url-status=live }}</ref> At the [[2021 Dutch Grand Prix|Dutch Grand Prix]] Verstappen again qualified on pole, beating Hamilton by 0.038 seconds.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Verstappen says technical issues prevented Dutch GP pole lap being even faster around 'incredible' Zandvoort|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.verstappen-says-technical-issues-prevented-pole-lap-being-even-faster-around.63hSAhZT8QfMy86azal66v.html|access-date=19 January 2022|publisher=Formula One|archive-date=18 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220118232921/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.verstappen-says-technical-issues-prevented-pole-lap-being-even-faster-around.63hSAhZT8QfMy86azal66v.html|url-status=live}}</ref> During the race Verstappen was able to fend off attacks from both Mercedes drivers to take the win, taking the lead in the Drivers' Championship by three points.<ref name="RedBull.com">{{cite web | title=Dutch Grand Prix 2021: race report and reaction | website=RedBull.com | url=https://www.redbull.com/int-en/dutch-f1-grand-prix-2021-race-report | access-date=18 December 2021 | archive-date=18 December 2021 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211218075510/https://www.redbull.com/int-en/dutch-f1-grand-prix-2021-race-report | url-status=live }}</ref> For the {{F1GP|2021|Russian}}, Verstappen was required to start at the back of the grid for exceeding his quota of power unit components.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Verstappen set to start Russian GP from the back of the grid after engine change|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.verstappen-set-to-start-russian-gp-from-the-back-of-the-grid-after-engine.7f6jFpCcP8YyCh2A8UEGMw.html|url-status=live|access-date=26 September 2021|publisher=Formula One|archive-date=30 October 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211030080928/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.verstappen-set-to-start-russian-gp-from-the-back-of-the-grid-after-engine.7f6jFpCcP8YyCh2A8UEGMw.html}}</ref> He made his way back up the field, and after taking an early pit stop for intermediate tyres late in the race, he finished second.<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://www.thecheckeredflag.co.uk/2021/09/max-verstappen-we-made-a-great-decision-with-the-timing-and-took-the-right-lap-to-pit/|title = Max Verstappen: "We made a great decision with the timing and took the right lap to pit"|date = 27 September 2021|access-date = 27 September 2021|archive-date = 27 September 2021|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210927094249/https://www.thecheckeredflag.co.uk/2021/09/max-verstappen-we-made-a-great-decision-with-the-timing-and-took-the-right-lap-to-pit/|url-status = live}}</ref> At the [[2021 Turkish Grand Prix|Turkish Grand Prix]], Verstappen qualified second with Bottas on pole.<ref>{{Cite web|date=9 October 2021|title=Valtteri Bottas gets Turkish F1 GP pole in boost for fastest man Lewis Hamilton|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2021/oct/09/valtteri-bottas-turkish-f1-gp-pole-lewis-hamilton-max-verstappen|access-date=19 January 2022|website=The Guardian|archive-date=9 October 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211009132422/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2021/oct/09/valtteri-bottas-turkish-f1-gp-pole-lewis-hamilton-max-verstappen|url-status=live}}</ref> With the race being run in wet conditions and the drivers on intermediate tyres the whole race, Verstappen finished second behind Bottas, taking the lead in the Drivers' Championship by six points as Hamilton finished fifth.<ref>{{cite web |last=Benson |first=Andrew |title=Turkish Grand Prix: Valtteri Bottas wins as Max Verstappen retakes title lead |publisher=BBC Sport |date=10 October 2021 |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/formula1/58863226 |access-date=23 October 2021 |archive-date=22 October 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211022194759/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/formula1/58863226 |url-status=live }}</ref> 
[[File:2021 United States Grand Prix 23.jpg|thumb|Verstappen battling with Lewis Hamilton for the lead at the 2021 United States Grand Prix]]
At the [[2021 United States Grand Prix|United States Grand Prix]], Verstappen took pole position in qualifying, edging Hamilton by 0.209 seconds.<ref>{{Cite web|title=2021 United States Grand Prix qualifying report and highlights: Verstappen beats Hamilton to pole position with sensational final lap in Austin|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.qualifying-verstappen-pips-hamilton-to-pole-position-with-sensational-final.6zcE50igI0cWw2XVigtY6x.html|access-date=19 January 2022|publisher=Formula One|archive-date=8 December 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211208094708/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.qualifying-verstappen-pips-hamilton-to-pole-position-with-sensational-final.6zcE50igI0cWw2XVigtY6x.html|url-status=live}}</ref> Verstappen won the race and extended his lead in the Drivers' Championship to twelve points as Hamilton finished second with the fastest lap.<ref name="BBC Sport 2021">{{cite web | title=Title battle heads into its climax | publisher=BBC Sport | date=25 October 2021 | url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/formula1/59032201 | access-date=18 December 2021 | archive-date=18 December 2021 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211218072035/https://www.bbc.com/sport/formula1/59032201 | url-status=live }}</ref> At the [[2021 Mexico City Grand Prix]], Verstappen qualified third with a gap to pole-sitter Bottas of 0.350 seconds.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Mexico City qualifying: Mercedes shock Red Bull as Bottas takes pole ahead of Hamilton|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.qualifying-mercedes-shock-red-bull-as-bottas-takes-pole-ahead-of-hamilton-in.2dTyrMJFp6YU4FliMrIYQ0.html|access-date=19 January 2022|publisher=Formula One|archive-date=5 December 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211205223654/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.qualifying-mercedes-shock-red-bull-as-bottas-takes-pole-ahead-of-hamilton-in.2dTyrMJFp6YU4FliMrIYQ0.html|url-status=live}}</ref> Verstappen's main opponent Hamilton qualified second. At the race start, Verstappen took the lead from Bottas and Hamilton into turn 1 and won the race, and as a result extended his lead in the championship to 19 points.<ref name="Fox Sports 2021">{{cite web | title=Hamilton has vowed to 'keep on fighting'. But his F1 crown is finally starting to slip | work=Fox Sports | date=8 November 2021 | url=https://www.foxsports.com.au/motorsport/formula-one/f1-news-mexico-grand-prix-2021-lewis-hamilton-max-verstappen-drivers-championship-standings-next-race-latest/news-story/9d8474f15bb968196e6b29d772b50f4c | access-date=18 December 2021 | archive-date=6 December 2021 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211206233354/https://www.foxsports.com.au/motorsport/formula-one/f1-news-mexico-grand-prix-2021-lewis-hamilton-max-verstappen-drivers-championship-standings-next-race-latest/news-story/9d8474f15bb968196e6b29d772b50f4c | url-status=live }}</ref>

Verstappen and Hamilton were on equal points in the Drivers' Championship going into the final round,<ref>{{Cite web|title=How can Lewis Hamilton win the 2021 F1 title?|url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/how-can-lewis-hamilton-win-the-2021-f1-title/6857947/|access-date=12 February 2022|website=Autosport|date=6 December 2021 |language=en|archive-date=12 February 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220212104346/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/how-can-lewis-hamilton-win-the-2021-f1-title/6857947/|url-status=live}}</ref> the {{F1GP|2021|Abu Dhabi}}, with Verstappen leading on countback. Verstappen overtook Hamilton on the final lap to win the race, and his first Formula One World Drivers' Championship.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/live/2021/dec/12/f1-abu-dhabi-grand-prix-formula-one-max-verstappen-lewis-hamilton-title-live-updates|title=Abu Dhabi GP: Max Verstappen wins F1 world title after last-lap drama – live!|first=Daniel|last=Harris|date=13 December 2021|access-date=13 December 2021|website=[[The Guardian]]|archive-date=12 December 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211212200746/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/live/2021/dec/12/f1-abu-dhabi-grand-prix-formula-one-max-verstappen-lewis-hamilton-title-live-updates|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|title=Verstappen Wins Title With Final Lap Overtake! {{!}} 2021 Abu Dhabi Grand Prix|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MTe12fH2xtQ|access-date=20 January 2022|archive-date=20 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220120013017/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MTe12fH2xtQ|url-status=live}}</ref> Verstappen, who had qualified on pole position by nearly four-tenths of a second, had a slow start off the line at the start of the race and dropped to second place. Verstappen was trailing Hamilton by over ten seconds until a late safety car was called in due to a crash at turn 14 involving Williams driver [[Nicholas Latifi]].<ref>{{Citation|title=Race Highlights {{!}} 2021 Abu Dhabi Grand Prix|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7QJ-N-AQJYc|access-date=20 January 2022|archive-date=13 October 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221013203428/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7QJ-N-AQJYc|url-status=live}}</ref> The withdrawal of the safety car and the resumption of the race following the safety car period was met with controversy. Race director [[Michael Masi]] allowed only a certain number of lapped cars through, which after the race brought from the Mercedes team a protest and stated intention to appeal against the race result, arguing that all lapped cars should be allowed through, Red Bull counter argued that this was not specified by the wording of the regulations. The protest was rejected, although subsequent investigation by the FIA resulted in the wording of the rule being amended for the 2022 season to specify that "all" cars will unlap themselves (at the race director's discretion) rather than "any".<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.fia.com/sites/default/files/doc_58_-_2021_abu_dhabi_grand_prix_-_decision_-_mercedes_protest_art._48.12.pdf |title= Decision – Mercedes Protest Art. 48.12 |date= 12 December 2021 |publisher= [[Fédération Internationale de l'Automobile]] |access-date= 19 December 2021 |archive-date= 12 December 2021 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20211212191155/https://www.fia.com/sites/default/files/doc_58_-_2021_abu_dhabi_grand_prix_-_decision_-_mercedes_protest_art._48.12.pdf |url-status= live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=19 March 2022 |title=2021 F1 Abu Dhabi Grand Prix – Report to the World Motor Sport Council – 19 March 2022 |url=https://www.fia.com/2021-f1-abu-dhabi-grand-prix-report-world-motor-sport-council-19-march-2022 |access-date=25 March 2022 |website=[[Federation Internationale de l'Automobile]] |archive-date=24 March 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220324224707/https://www.fia.com/2021-f1-abu-dhabi-grand-prix-report-world-motor-sport-council-19-march-2022 |url-status=live}}</ref> Verstappen passed Hamilton at turn 5 of the final lap of the race to become the 34th Formula One World Drivers' Champion.<ref>{{Cite news|url = https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/formula1/59628024|title = Max Verstappen wins title after last-lap overtake of Lewis Hamilton, Mercedes protests rejected|publisher = BBC Sport|date = 12 December 2021|access-date = 14 December 2021|archive-date = 14 December 2021|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20211214231835/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/formula1/59628024|url-status = live}}</ref>
[[File:RB18 JapaneseGP FP2.jpg|thumb|Verstappen at the [[2022 Japanese Grand Prix]], where he won his second World Drivers' Championship]]

==== 2022 season: Dominant second title ====
{{expand section|date=July 2023}}
In March 2022, Verstappen signed a five-year contract extension with Red Bull Racing for the 2023 to 2028 seasons.<ref name=":3" />

Verstappen suffered two fuel system related retirements in the first three races, finding himself 46 points behind championship leader Charles Leclerc. He responded by winning five of the next seven races, allowing him to take the championship lead and build a gap of 37 points over second place, by then held by his teammate Sergio Pérez. He would go on to dominate much of the [[2022 Formula One World Championship|season]], winning 15 races, securing the World Drivers' Championship at the [[2022 Japanese Grand Prix|Japanese Grand Prix]].<ref name="Morlidge 2022">{{cite web | last=Morlidge | first=Matt | title=Max Verstappen crowned 2022 F1 world champion amid Japanese GP confusion after winning wet race | publisher=Sky Sports | date=9 October 2022 | url=https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/12707671/max-verstappen-crowned-2022-f1-world-champion-amid-japanese-gp-confusion-after-winning-wet-race | access-date=9 October 2022 | archive-date=9 October 2022 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221009090638/https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/12707671/max-verstappen-crowned-2022-f1-world-champion-amid-japanese-gp-confusion-after-winning-wet-race | url-status=live }}</ref> He achieved a [[grand slam (Formula One)|grand slam]] at the [[2022 Emilia Romagna Grand Prix]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Kelly |first=Sean |date=24 April 2022 |title=Facts and Stats: A grand slam first, and Red Bull's maiden double score at Imola |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.facts-and-stats-a-grand-slam-first-and-red-bulls-maiden-double-score-at.7nAGUuihqzKZA9PoyCUCf6.html |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220712125614/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.facts-and-stats-a-grand-slam-first-and-red-bulls-maiden-double-score-at.7nAGUuihqzKZA9PoyCUCf6.html |archive-date=12 July 2022 |access-date=7 July 2022 |publisher=Formula One}}</ref>

==== 2023 season: Record-breaking dominance and third title====
[[File:FIA F1 Austria 2023 Race (1).jpg|thumb|left|Verstappen leading the race at the [[2023 Austrian Grand Prix]]]]
Verstappen remained with Red Bull alongside Sergio Pérez for the 2023 season. Verstappen achieved consistently high results throughout the season, setting several Formula One records, including his win at the [[2023 Hungarian Grand Prix|Hungarian Grand Prix]], which broke the record for most consecutive wins by a constructor at twelve, previously held by McLaren in 1988 with eleven,<ref>{{cite web |last=Kelly |first=Sean |title=Facts and stats: Red Bull records aplenty as champions take 250th podium |publisher=Formula 1 |date=23 July 2023 |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.facts-and-stats-red-bull-records-aplenty-as-champions-take-250th-podium.2dswmYrFo2LpGo496G0b4S.html |access-date=23 July 2023 |archive-date=23 July 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230723170820/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.facts-and-stats-red-bull-records-aplenty-as-champions-take-250th-podium.2dswmYrFo2LpGo496G0b4S.html |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/f1-hungarian-gp-verstappen-streaks-to-win-as-red-bull-claims-12th-successive-win/10499222/ |title=F1 British GP: Verstappen streaks to win as Red Bull claims 12th successive win |last=Boxall-Legge |first=Jake |date=23 July 2023 |website=Autosport.com |access-date=21 September 2023 |archive-date=24 July 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230724002612/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/f1-hungarian-gp-verstappen-streaks-to-win-as-red-bull-claims-12th-successive-win/10499222/ |url-status=live }}</ref> and the [[2023 Italian Grand Prix|Italian Grand Prix]], which marked his tenth consecutive win, breaking [[Sebastian Vettel]]'s previous record of nine set in 2013.<ref>{{cite web |last=Richards |first=Giles |url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/sep/03/max-verstappen-wins-record-10th-straight-race-with-italian-f1-gp-victory |title=Max Verstappen wins record 10th straight race with Italian F1 GP victory |work=The Guardian |date=3 September 2023 |access-date=4 September 2023 |archive-date=4 September 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230904230308/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/sep/03/max-verstappen-wins-record-10th-straight-race-with-italian-f1-gp-victory |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.verstappen-charges-to-monza-victory-for-record-breaking-10th-successive-f1.6jCUOTZ4lZB3kxfIiwsiHK.html |title=Verstappen charges to Monza victory for record-breaking 10th successive F1 win |date=3 September 2023 |website=Formula One |author=Formula One Management |access-date=21 September 2023 |archive-date=3 September 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230903164334/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.verstappen-charges-to-monza-victory-for-record-breaking-10th-successive-f1.6jCUOTZ4lZB3kxfIiwsiHK.html |url-status=live }}</ref> His ten consecutive wins include a [[grand slam (Formula One)|grand slam]] at the [[2023 Spanish Grand Prix]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Mee |first=Lydia |date=4 June 2023 |title=Spanish Grand Prix Results: Mercedes Shocks With Insane Comeback |url=https://www.si.com/fannation/racing/f1briefings/news/spanish-grand-prix-results-mercedes-shocks-with-insane-comeback-lm22 |access-date=4 June 2023 |website=F1 Briefings: Formula 1 News, Rumors, Standings and More |language=en |archive-date=4 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230604145708/https://www.si.com/fannation/racing/f1briefings/news/spanish-grand-prix-results-mercedes-shocks-with-insane-comeback-lm22 |url-status=live }}</ref> After a brief slump in [[2023 Singapore Grand Prix|Singapore]] - which saw him finish fifth and his [[List of Formula One driver records#Most consecutive wins|record-setting streak of ten consecutive wins]] be broken<ref>{{Cite web |title=Sainz takes sensational Singapore Grand Prix victory |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.sainz-holds-off-norris-and-fast-charging-mercedes-pair-to-take-sensational.16sNsRUz2MAFyXxSE3RdwX.html |access-date=18 September 2023 |website=www.formula1.com |language=en |archive-date=17 September 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230917160814/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.sainz-holds-off-norris-and-fast-charging-mercedes-pair-to-take-sensational.16sNsRUz2MAFyXxSE3RdwX.html |url-status=live }}</ref> - Verstappen took pole position once again in [[2023 Japanese Grand Prix|Suzuka]], the track where he achieved his 2022 title, and led the field ahead of [[Lando Norris]] and [[Oscar Piastri]] to secure Red Bull Racing its sixth Constructors' Championship title - and also Red Bull's second consecutive title after its victory in 2022.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Richards |first=Giles |date=24 September 2023 |title=Max Verstappen on verge of F1 world title after winning Japanese Grand Prix |language=en-GB |work=The Guardian |url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/sep/24/max-verstappen-on-brink-of-f1-world-title-after-winning-japanese-grand-prix |access-date=25 September 2023 |issn=0261-3077 |archive-date=26 September 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230926114547/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/sep/24/max-verstappen-on-brink-of-f1-world-title-after-winning-japanese-grand-prix |url-status=live }}</ref> During the sprint for the following [[2023 Qatar Grand Prix|Qatar Grand Prix]], Verstappen finished second from [[Oscar Piastri]] while Pérez did not finish, handing the 2023 Drivers' Championship to Verstappen,<ref>{{Cite web |date=7 October 2023 |title=Verstappen secures third F1 world title as Piastri takes Sprint victory in Qatar |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.verstappen-secures-third-f1-world-title-as-piastri-takes-sprint-victory-in.4d0SLopnXU9W8uzefnJmu3.html |access-date=8 October 2023 |website=Formula1.com |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231011012612/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.verstappen-secures-third-f1-world-title-as-piastri-takes-sprint-victory-in.4d0SLopnXU9W8uzefnJmu3.html |archive-date=11 October 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> who joined [[Juan Manuel Fangio]], [[Jack Brabham]], [[Graham Hill]], [[Keke Rosberg]], and [[Nelson Piquet]] as the only drivers to have won a championship on a Saturday.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Baldwin |first=Alan |date=4 October 2023 |title=Verstappen can join the ranks of F1's Saturday champions |url=https://www.reuters.com/sports/motor-sports/verstappen-can-be-saturday-champion-just-like-piquet-2023-10-04/ |access-date=8 October 2023 |website=Reuters.com|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231009044448/https://www.reuters.com/sports/motor-sports/verstappen-can-be-saturday-champion-just-like-piquet-2023-10-04/|archive-date=9 October 2023|url-status=live}}</ref>

==Reception==
===Qualifying speed===
[[File:2018 Chinese Grand Prix Qualifying Max Verstappen (27842985498).jpg|thumb|Verstappen on a qualifying lap at the [[2018 Chinese Grand Prix]]]]
Following Verstappen's maiden pole position at the 2019 Hungarian Grand Prix, former Formula One World Champion Nico Rosberg described him as the fastest driver in Formula One. Rosberg elucidated that Verstappen did not have the fastest car during the qualifying session in Hungary, emphasising that it was Verstappen's raw speed that allowed him to secure pole position: "Mercedes still had the fastest car, and it's just Verstappen with his driving that put it up there in pole."<ref>{{Citation|title=5 reasons why Verstappen is currently the fastest F1 driver {{!}} Hungarian GP Qualifying Analysis|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VLGlqQOhZ2Y|access-date=7 January 2022|archive-date=13 October 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221013205356/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VLGlqQOhZ2Y|url-status=live}}</ref>

In 2019, former Formula One World Champion [[Jenson Button]] stated that he believes Verstappen is the fastest Formula One driver ever: "I think he is the fastest driver that has ever driven an F1 car. I really do, I think he is unbelievably fast."<ref>{{Cite web|date=17 October 2019|title=Button says Verstappen is the fastest F1 driver ever|url=https://www.espn.com/f1/story/_/id/27867007/verstappen-fastest-f1-driver-ever|url-status=live|publisher=ESPN|access-date=7 January 2022|archive-date=8 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220108224915/https://www.espn.com/f1/story/_/id/27867007/verstappen-fastest-f1-driver-ever}}</ref> Journalist Scott Mitchell from ''The Race'' commented: "When everything comes together, Verstappen is the quickest driver in F1 over one lap, but the odd mistake and scruffy session must be eliminated."<ref>{{Cite web|date=10 February 2020|title=Ranking Leclerc and Verstappen in the fight to topple Hamilton|url=https://the-race.com/formula-1/ranking-leclerc-and-verstappen-in-the-fight-to-topple-hamilton/|access-date=8 January 2022|website=The Race|archive-date=8 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220108192416/https://the-race.com/formula-1/ranking-leclerc-and-verstappen-in-the-fight-to-topple-hamilton/|url-status=live}}</ref> Helmut Marko, head of Red Bull's driver development programme, stated that Verstappen is the fastest driver Red Bull have ever had.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Max Verstappen looking set for F1 2020 at Red Bull |url=https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/11775650/max-verstappen-looking-set-for-f1-2020-at-red-bull |access-date=18 August 2022 |publisher=Sky Sports |language=en |archive-date=18 August 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220818170804/https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/11775650/max-verstappen-looking-set-for-f1-2020-at-red-bull |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Marko rates the best and worst traits of Red Bull's F1 stars |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/marko-rates-the-best-and-worst-traits-of-red-bulls-f1-stars/10334712/amp/ |access-date=18 August 2022 |website=Autosport |date=8 July 2022 |language=en |archive-date=18 August 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220818170804/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/marko-rates-the-best-and-worst-traits-of-red-bulls-f1-stars/10334712/amp/ |url-status=live }}</ref> In 2021, three-time Formula One World Champion [[Jackie Stewart]] claimed that Verstappen is the fastest driver in Formula One, but he also added that Verstappen is still in the "puppy stage" of his career.<ref>{{Cite web|date=16 September 2021|title=Verstappen now 'fastest driver in the business', Jackie Stewart claims|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/motor-racing/formula1/max-verstappen-lewis-hamilton-jackie-stewart-f1-b1921212.html |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220512/https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/motor-racing/formula1/max-verstappen-lewis-hamilton-jackie-stewart-f1-b1921212.html |archive-date=12 May 2022 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live|access-date=7 January 2022|website=The Independent}}</ref> [[Peter Windsor]], an experienced Formula One journalist, expressed Verstappen's ability to change direction "quicker than anybody else" through the high-speed section Maggots and Becketts: Silverstone's fastest sequence of corners. Windsor stressed that Verstappen's lightning-quick change of direction is a result of the innate feel he has for creating the "perfect platform" to achieve what he wants with the car during a lap. He is intrinsically able to create, for "a trillionth of a second", a minuscule "flat area" between the left and the right of a change of direction ahead of him, in order to attain a stable balance with the car before applying the next steering and throttle input.<ref>{{Citation|title=If Max is an early braker why is he so fast? By Peter Windsor|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=M7AgJXQ2rEI|access-date=13 January 2022|archive-date=11 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220111082058/https://www.youtube.com/watch?app=desktop&v=M7AgJXQ2rEI|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Scuderia AlphaTauri]]'s team principal, [[Franz Tost]], declared Verstappen to be the fastest driver in Formula One; following the Dutchman's "really deserved" maiden title triumph in 2021.<ref name="Woodhouse2021">{{cite news |last1=Woodhouse |first1=Jamie |title=Franz Tost: 'Fastest driver' Max Verstappen deserved his Formula 1 world title |url=https://www.planetf1.com/news/franz-tost-max-verstappen-deserved-title |access-date=25 October 2023 |work=PlanetF1 |date=14 December 2021 |language=en |archive-date=6 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221206183802/https://www.planetf1.com/news/franz-tost-max-verstappen-deserved-title/ |url-status=live }}</ref> On the subject of sim racing, Verstappen was deemed the "fastest" driver by [[IndyCar Series|IndyCar]] racer and former Formula One driver Romain Grosjean.<ref>{{Cite web|last=GPfans.com|title=Grosjean would like Verstappen in his sim team: He is the fastest|url=https://www.gpfans.com/nl/f1-nieuws/60667/grosjean-zou-verstappen-wel-in-zijn-sim-team-willen-hij-is-het-snelst/|access-date=13 January 2022|website=GPfans|date=21 December 2020 |language=nl|archive-date=13 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220113111909/https://www.gpfans.com/nl/f1-nieuws/60667/grosjean-zou-verstappen-wel-in-zijn-sim-team-willen-hij-is-het-snelst/|url-status=live}}</ref>

===Dominance over teammates===
[[File:Red Bull duo 2016 Malaysia Race.jpg|left|thumb|Verstappen racing with then teammate Daniel Ricciardo at the [[2016 Malaysian Grand Prix]]]]
Former Formula One driver [[Eddie Irvine]] praised Verstappen, stating that he is "by far the most dominant team leader on the grid." Irvine highlighted that Verstappen "has had many different second drivers in the team and none of them have got close to him."<ref name="Sharan2021Irvine">{{cite news |last1=Sharan |first1=Rahul |title=Irvine finds similarities between Verstappen and Schumacher |url=https://racingnews365.com/irvine-finds-similarities-between-verstappen-and-schumacher |access-date=25 October 2023 |work=RacingNews365 |date=10 June 2021 |language=en |archive-date=14 June 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210614105847/https://racingnews365.com/irvine-finds-similarities-between-verstappen-and-schumacher |url-status=live }}</ref> During the 2020 season, Jenson Button stated that he doesn't "think there's been a driver that's annihilated their team-mates like he [Verstappen] has in a very long time."<ref>{{Cite web|title=Button: Verstappen &quot;annihilating&quot; team-mates like Senna|url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/button-verstappen-annihilating-team-mates-like-senna-4979817/4979817/|access-date=13 January 2022|website=Autosport|date=25 August 2020 |archive-date=13 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220113084508/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/button-verstappen-annihilating-team-mates-like-senna-4979817/4979817/|url-status=live}}</ref> Motorsport columnist and former Formula One driver [[Jolyon Palmer]], commented that Verstappen's maiden world championship triumph could usher in a "new era of dominance" in the sport. Palmer wrote:<blockquote>[Verstappen's] qualifying pace is frightening and has been the basis for this title-charging campaign. He's had the most pole positions of anyone with 10 – almost half of the races, and it would have been half had he completed his mesmeric Jeddah lap, which ended up being possibly Max's biggest error in a near-perfect season. For a driver who has demolished three successive team mates in three years and made only a handful of small mistakes in that time, you question what scope their even is for improvement – but if he can take his game onto another level from here, we could be about to see the start of a new era of dominance.<ref>{{Cite web|title=PALMER: Whatever you thought of the Abu Dhabi outcome, Verstappen was a worthy champion in 2021|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.palmer-whatever-you-thought-of-the-abu-dhabi-outcome-verstappen-was-a-worthy.6RkHgJTJgx8HjlqwPraGo0.html|access-date=2022-01-27|publisher=Formula One|language=en|archive-date=13 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220113090926/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.palmer-whatever-you-thought-of-the-abu-dhabi-outcome-verstappen-was-a-worthy.6RkHgJTJgx8HjlqwPraGo0.html|url-status=live}}</ref></blockquote>Journalist Scott Mitchell expounded the reason why the Dutchman's teammates have fallen short "even with the data." Mitchell wrote: "Verstappen drives mainly on intuition, and that comes from years of training and preparation. He has a database in his head which he can use immediately. Even with data, Gasly and Albon could see where he was faster, but they could never grasp how he was faster there. That's because what makes Verstappen so good is mainly unconscious." According to Mitchell, those years of training and driving on his intuition has made it impossible for other drivers to measure up to Verstappen.<ref>{{Cite web|date=19 January 2021|title=Verstappen 'driving style' myth is a trait of greatness|url=https://the-race.com/formula-1/verstappen-driving-style-myth-is-a-trait-of-greatness/|access-date=13 January 2022|website=The Race|archive-date=15 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220115064106/https://the-race.com/formula-1/verstappen-driving-style-myth-is-a-trait-of-greatness/|url-status=live}}</ref>

Helmut Marko, the current advisor to the [[Red Bull GmbH]] Formula One teams,<ref>{{Cite web|last=Delaney|first=Michael|date=3 November 2019|title=No retirement in sight for the good Dr. Marko|url=https://f1i.com/news/360631-no-retirement-in-sight-for-the-good-dr-marko.html|access-date=15 January 2022|website=F1i.com|archive-date=19 December 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191219183556/https://f1i.com/news/360631-no-retirement-in-sight-for-the-good-dr-marko.html|url-status=live}}</ref> asserted that Verstappen's progress has moved him clear of his former Formula 1 team-mate Daniel Ricciardo, in both qualifying and race trim. "There is specific data," Marko told Autosport, "In qualifying the gap to Ricciardo is greater. The strange thing is Max sometimes slides more, but still manages to keep the tyres alive." Verstappen previously mentioned that he was three or four-tenths faster on average than "very fast qualifier" Daniel Ricciardo.<ref>{{Cite web|last=GMM|date=28 September 2017|title=Max Verstappen says he's considerably faster than Red Bull F1 teammate Daniel Ricciardo|url=http://autoweek.com/racing/formula-1/a1831511/max-verstappen-says-hes-considerably-faster-red-bull-f1-teammate-daniel/|access-date=15 January 2022|website=Autoweek|archive-date=15 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220115065822/https://www.autoweek.com/racing/formula-1/a1831511/max-verstappen-says-hes-considerably-faster-red-bull-f1-teammate-daniel/|url-status=live}}</ref> Marko concluded that then 20-year-old Verstappen "clearly moved away" from Ricciardo since the "second half of the 2018 season."<ref>{{Cite web|title=Marko: Verstappen moved clear of ex-Red Bull F1 team-mate Ricciardo|url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/marko-verstappen-moved-clear-of-ex-red-bull-f1-team-mate-ricciardo-5282660/5282660/|access-date=15 January 2022|website=Autosport|date=13 January 2019 |archive-date=15 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220115032851/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/marko-verstappen-moved-clear-of-ex-red-bull-f1-team-mate-ricciardo-5282660/5282660/|url-status=live}}</ref>

===Natural talent===
[[File:Podium 2017 Malaysia.jpg|thumb|Verstappen on the podium with Hamilton (left) and Ricciardo (right) after winning the [[2017 Malaysian Grand Prix]]]]
Following his maiden Formula One win, at the [[2016 Spanish Grand Prix]], three-time Formula One World Champion [[Niki Lauda]] described Verstappen as the "talent of the century."<ref>{{cite web|title=Niki Lauda calls Max Verstappen the 'talent of the century'|url=https://www.autoweek.com/racing/formula-1/a1846031/niki-lauda-calls-f1-driver-max-verstappen-talent-century/|website=autoweek.com|date=16 May 2016|access-date=28 January 2022|archive-date=28 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220128125836/https://www.autoweek.com/racing/formula-1/a1846031/niki-lauda-calls-f1-driver-max-verstappen-talent-century/|url-status=live}}</ref> Red Bull Team Principal Christian Horner stated that Verstappen is the best driver Red Bull have ever seen: "I have no doubt [Verstappen is] the best we have seen on one of our cars, in terms of outright raw ability and commitment. He's the best driver we’ve seen."<ref>{{Cite web |title=Horner on the 'rare' quality Verstappen shares with Hamilton |url=https://racingnews365.com/horner-on-the-rare-quality-verstappen-shares-with-hamilton |access-date=18 August 2022 |website=RacingNews365 |date=10 January 2022 |language=en |archive-date=18 August 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220818175204/https://racingnews365.com/horner-on-the-rare-quality-verstappen-shares-with-hamilton |url-status=live }}</ref>

Former Formula One driver [[Gerhard Berger]] echoed Jenson Button's recent comments, anointing Max Verstappen as the Formula One driver of this era with the most raw talent. Speaking to ''Sport1'', Berger ventured: “When it comes to raw talent, Max Verstappen is the most talented of all. But it’s not just about raw talent, it’s about the whole package. That means it’s not just about setting the fastest laps but also to win a race. And not just [about] one race but many and eventually a championship, and championships."<ref>{{Cite web|date=15 June 2021|title=Berger: Verstappen probably has most raw talent of all|url=https://www.grandprix247.com/2021/06/15/gerhard-berger-says-when-it-comes-to-raw-talent-max-verstappen-is-probably-on-top-of-it-all/|access-date=8 January 2022|website=GRAND PRIX 247|archive-date=8 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220108010013/https://www.grandprix247.com/2021/06/15/gerhard-berger-says-when-it-comes-to-raw-talent-max-verstappen-is-probably-on-top-of-it-all/|url-status=live}}</ref> Two-time Formula One World Champion Fernando Alonso commented that Verstappen is the standout driver in Formula One, declaring the Red Bull star to be "one step ahead" of everyone. Alonso noted that Verstappen deserved to win the Formula One drivers’ championship in Abu Dhabi, ahead of the title decider that saw the Dutchman and Lewis Hamilton enter level on points: “Mercedes lately have been more performing and they’ve won a couple of races now, but Max is driving – in my opinion – one step ahead of all of us. We saw the [qualifying] lap in Jeddah, until he touched the wall at the last corner, that lap was coming from Max, not the Red Bull."<ref>{{Cite web|title=Alonso believes Verstappen 'driving one step ahead of everyone' as he says Dutchman 'deserves' 2021 title|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.alonso-believes-verstappen-driving-one-step-ahead-of-everyone-as-he-says.2j28pfrHJJlpCfuykTmw0T.html|access-date=12 January 2022|publisher=Formula One|archive-date=12 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220112054056/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.alonso-believes-verstappen-driving-one-step-ahead-of-everyone-as-he-says.2j28pfrHJJlpCfuykTmw0T.html|url-status=live}}</ref> Former Formula One Driver [[Karun Chandhok]] likened Verstappen's ruthless and uncompromising attitude in race combat to Michael Schumacher's unyielding and iron-willed style of racing.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Chandhok |first1=Karun |title=Karun Chandhok's top 10 Formula 1 drivers of the 2021 season: Who makes the cut after epic year? |url=https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/36347/12498220/karun-chandhoks-top-10-formula-1-drivers-of-the-2021-season-who-makes-the-cut-after-epic-year |newspaper=Sky Sports |access-date=18 December 2021 |archive-date=18 December 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211218102740/https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/36347/12498220/karun-chandhoks-top-10-formula-1-drivers-of-the-2021-season-who-makes-the-cut-after-epic-year |url-status=live }}</ref> Verstappen was ranked first in the annual Formula One team principals’ top ten drivers ranking in 2021.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Verstappen tops Autosport's F1 team boss rankings for 2021|url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/verstappen-tops-autosports-f1-team-boss-rankings-for-2021/6886514/|access-date=17 January 2022|website=Autosport|date=18 December 2021 |archive-date=8 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220108122236/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/verstappen-tops-autosports-f1-team-boss-rankings-for-2021/6886514/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=REVEALED: F1's team bosses choose their Top 10 drivers of 2021|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.revealed-f1s-team-bosses-choose-their-top-10-drivers-of-2021.1sK8ysV0LK0MIbeNsHAkgY.html|access-date=17 January 2022|publisher=Formula One|archive-date=15 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220115200559/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.revealed-f1s-team-bosses-choose-their-top-10-drivers-of-2021.1sK8ysV0LK0MIbeNsHAkgY.html|url-status=live}}</ref>

===Racecraft===
Following Verstappen being given a warning for his driving conduct at the 2016 Belgian Grand Prix, the 18-year-old received the backing of then three-time champion Lewis Hamilton, who commented: "firstly, give the guy a break, he is 18 years old. What the frickin' heck were any of us doing at 18?"<ref>{{cite web |title=Verstappen Welcomes Support From Hamilton |url=https://news.sky.com/story/verstappen-welcomes-support-from-hamilton-10567203 |publisher=Sky News |date=6 September 2016 |access-date=12 January 2022 |archive-date=5 February 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220205015109/https://news.sky.com/story/verstappen-welcomes-support-from-hamilton-10567203 |url-status=live }}</ref>

Despite earning high praise and acclaim from Formula One drivers and experts in and out of the sport, Verstappen faced criticism in the wake of the penalties he incurred during the [[2021 Saudi Arabian Grand Prix]]. Following this race, former Formula One driver [[Martin Brundle]] wrote: "Such is [his] car control and cunning, he's sometimes able to pull off the audacious moves and leave a margin of doubt as to whether it's hard racing or simply a professional foul outside of the regulations and it's those moments which are generating the confusion, controversies and inconsistencies. [[Ayrton Senna]] and Michael Schumacher had their faults too, and I was on the receiving end from both of them on occasions, but it's a sizeable dent on their immense reputations, not a positive."<ref>{{Cite web|title=Martin Brundle: Max Verstappen must stop these tactics vs Lewis Hamilton for his legacy... but what a title showdown we'll have|url=https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/24096/12488713/martin-brundle-max-verstappen-must-stop-these-tactics-vs-lewis-hamilton-for-his-legacy-but-what-a-title-showdown-well-have|access-date=9 January 2022|publisher=Sky Sports|archive-date=9 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220109043216/https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/24096/12488713/martin-brundle-max-verstappen-must-stop-these-tactics-vs-lewis-hamilton-for-his-legacy-but-what-a-title-showdown-well-have|url-status=live}}</ref> Following an impressive first half of the 2022 season, journalist [[David Tremayne]] claimed Verstappen had elevated himself to a new higher level compared to his 2021 title winning season, suggesting Verstappen's first title had made him more relaxed and "chirpy".<ref>{{cite web |last1=Tremayne |first1=David |title=TREMAYNE: Why 2022 Max Verstappen is an upgrade on the 2021 version |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.tremayne-why-2022-max-verstappen-is-an-upgrade-on-the-2021-version.6ajpJsL1vXqlNQMzTiTbtL.html |publisher=Formula One |access-date=4 August 2022 |archive-date=4 August 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220804135531/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.tremayne-why-2022-max-verstappen-is-an-upgrade-on-the-2021-version.6ajpJsL1vXqlNQMzTiTbtL.html |url-status=live }}</ref>

===Fan support===
[[File:FIA F1 Austria 2021 Post-Race Scene.jpg|thumb|Verstappen fans at the [[2021 Austrian Grand Prix]]]]
Verstappen has accumulated a significant fanbase from around the world, but in particular from his home country of the Netherlands. Grand Prix events have dedicated Verstappen [[grandstand]]s with thousands of travelling Dutch fans, boosting ticket sales particularly for European races such as Belgium, Austria and Hungary.<ref name="Smith 2018">{{cite web | last=Smith | first=Luke | title=The Max Factor: How Verstappen's fans have changed F1 | website=Crash | date=26 August 2018 | url=https://www.crash.net/f1/feature/904148/1/max-factor-how-verstappens-fans-have-changed-f1 | access-date=9 February 2022 | archive-date=9 February 2022 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220209210247/https://www.crash.net/f1/feature/904148/1/max-factor-how-verstappens-fans-have-changed-f1 | url-status=live }}</ref> During the 2021 Dutch Grand Prix, Honda's Formula One managing director Masashi Yamamoto praised the Verstappen supporters, saying that "in the six years I've been involved with Honda F1, I've never seen such a great turnout as at the Dutch Grand Prix. It was like being in a football stadium." He added that "when Max crossed the finish line first, the whole circuit coloured orange".<ref name="gpblog.com 2022">{{cite web | title=Honda impressed by Verstappen fans: 'Never seen such a great turnout' | website=gpblog.com | date=2 January 2022 | url=https://www.gpblog.com/en/news/102453/honda-impressed-by-verstappen-fans-never-seen-such-a-great-turnout.html | access-date=24 March 2022 | archive-date=23 February 2022 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220223034800/https://www.gpblog.com/en/news/102453/honda-impressed-by-verstappen-fans-never-seen-such-a-great-turnout.html | url-status=live }}</ref>

In 2021, Verstappen was voted the most popular Formula One driver in an official survey.<ref name="Galloway 2021">{{cite web | last=Galloway | first=James | title=F1 fan survey lists Max Verstappen as most-popular driver ahead of Lando Norris and Lewis Hamilton | publisher=Sky Sports | date=21 October 2021 | url=https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/12440256/f1-fan-survey-lists-max-verstappen-as-most-popular-driver-ahead-of-lando-norris-and-lewis-hamilton | access-date=24 March 2022 | archive-date=23 February 2022 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220223012214/https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/12440256/f1-fan-survey-lists-max-verstappen-as-most-popular-driver-ahead-of-lando-norris-and-lewis-hamilton | url-status=live }}</ref> He has a fan made song, "[[Super Max!]]" performed by {{Ill|Pitstop Boys|nl}}. The song went viral after his 2021 championship victory, reaching number two in the UK Spotify viral charts and fifth in the global one.<ref name="Gamble 2021">{{cite web | last=Gamble | first=Andrew | title=Verstappen's song 'Super Max' goes viral & enters Spotify's top charts | website=Daily Express | date=15 December 2021 | url=https://www.express.co.uk/sport/f1-autosport/1536642/Max-Verstappen-F1-song-Super-Max-goes-viral-Spotify-top-charts | access-date=12 September 2022 | archive-date=26 December 2021 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211226014407/https://www.express.co.uk/sport/f1-autosport/1536642/Max-Verstappen-F1-song-Super-Max-goes-viral-Spotify-top-charts | url-status=live }}</ref>

